comment: This class is unnecessarily tedious and difficult. Endless amount of policies to choose from to study, and this prof seemingly picks the most boring topics possible. Doesn't give clear guidelines or content of exams, the quizzes don't even match the readings, and was pretentious with occasional out of pocket things said. -900/10, don't recommend.

Many questions are completely ambiguous or have conflicting information which makes the midterm luck-based. Everyone ran out of time, average was initially an 80%. Now it's a 78%, and we're confused whether he curved it down? No lecture recs, mandatory attendance, midterms open at 9AM for 1 hour, & no slides released until weeks after his lectures.

She's clear as mud when it comes to everything--almost as if she is writing her dissertation on academic vagueness. Lectures are not mandatory but she throws in all sorts of attendance checks and participation activities, so you better attend. I was excited for the group project but I was stuck doing all of the work and it really dragged on.

Very unreasonable and harsh with grading group work. She would basically laugh us off when we went to her for help/clarification. She's absolutely brilliant and dedicated to her studies but I don't think she understood that her students aren't at the same level of knowledge as she is. She's moving to DC so luckily you probably won't have her.

Dr.  is a very difficult professor to work with and does not respect her students. When difficult situations arise in the classroom she's been shown to handle them extremely unfairly and without respect and careful consideration. If you're looking for fair treatment and respect from your professor I would not recommend Dr. .

I liked taking his class but I have to say it's quite repetitive. Yeah you learn a lot but it's super boring sometimes. You can easily pass the class with an A by just using sparknotes and not reading the 2 hours of homework he wants you to do by the next lecture. But he is very knowledgeable and friendly I liked him overall just kinda boring.
Really knows his stuff and interested in teaching. Don't take his class early in the day though, his voice will put you to sleep fast.
interesting - but monotonic...
He does know his stuff but do not get on his bad side. If you do he will undermine you in a passive aggressive way.

Independents and third-party supporters beware: this guy often confuses facts with opinions, whether or not his students realize it. He is quite biased against certain candidates and parties, yet some of the things he says contradict with his own biased statements-- apparently not enough to get him to change his mind.. What a letdown.

LOVED his class. Learned so much! He made it interesting by actually "talking" to the class and not lecturing in a monotone class. He has a sense of humor about things,but if ur not a "favorite" don't expect to be called on. My favorite PS class ever.
Do not even bother unless you are a democrat. Very Very liberal. Biggest name dropper in the world. Who the hell cares who Vern Riffe is, I sure don't. HAVE FUN!!!!

Prof. 's course is largely statistical and focuses on the kinda stuff most political science students probably already know (at least in a loose sense). As such, lectures are quite boring and most of the information can be gathered from skimming the slides he provides. He's terribly dry but very smart, so you can't really help but respect him.

Mr.  is very knowledgeable and enthusiastic about political parties. He is a great teacher, but sometimes his lectures can be a bit dry, boring, and repetitive. The two exams he gives are 25 multiple choice questions each with a long essay response as well. He also has you do a research paper that makes up a big portion of your grade.
Easy but boring.

The tests in this class were ridiculous, they are made up of totally random questions from the book. I found the lecture parts of the test to be quite easy, but his lectures are boring and the research is outdated. There is no new info to be learned in this class if you have already taken counseling psych and abnormal psych.

Dr.  was extremely spacey, disorganized and dull. His lectures sometimes have information that is incorrect and misleading. He relies HEAVILY on insignificant details from the book. If you read the book then that part of the test is fine, but the lecture section is ridiculous. The paper, however, was easy.

The class is not hard if you life cold hard stats. Half of exam comes from the book (which you never go over and is indep study) and lectures that are based on date he has found on diff. subjects. He comes off anxious and is pretty scatter-brained, unprepared. His off the cuff style does not work. 3 exams and a an easy paper. Take only if needed.
This professor constantly generalizes about disorders, uses outdated research, and is super terrible at writing exams. good luck, i would not recommend him, he needs to retire

This man has no buisiness being a college proffesor.
  If a student asks a question which he doesn't know the answer to, he just guesses, often times wrongly.
  The subject matter is very easy to master, yet it is nearly impossible to get an A. This is because his tests include many random and irrelavent statistics from the text book.

Very, very boring lectures. Stays on the same slide for an hour. Attendance does matter because you do writing assignments in each class. Very boring and drawn out talks but easy class. Tests aren't too bad as long as you study.

Overall a pretty easy class if you do the readings and attend class to complete critical thinking written assignments (1-2 paragraphs). Lectures are extremely boring. I think this class could be really interesting if taught by a different professor. If you want to attend jailprison tours, don't schedule class after this one.
Boring. Bad use of powerpoint.
Extremely boring teacher, speaks mono-tone the whole time. Makes harder to understand than it should be.

The previous two post say it well. He stands in front of the class and simply lectures from the book, he's more than boring, and he makes the class harder than it needs to be. He does provide his slides but not until a couple days before the test. He gives absolutely NO review and you're on your own for the tests. Very disappointed in this teacher.

3 MC tests. Seemed to stretch for material on a few of the questions. Lectures were pretty boring. Had 1-3 opinion questions that you had to hand in at the end of each class. Just hand in something and you are good. These were worth a solid % of the grade and worth the effort.
is an extremely boring lecturer, however her exams are made up of exactly what is posted on the slides, so memorize these! You do not need to attend lecture to get a good grade in this class.

Dr.  is funny & relatable, but I did not like his course, he's unprofessional and swears a lot, and although the tests are relatively easy, the format rubbed me the wrong way. Plus, when I took his class, I missed a thing or a religious holiday, and he wouldn't let me make it up. That assignment was the difference between an A- and B+ for me.

Terrible terrible terrible terrible professor!!!! I can't even explain how much I hated his class. I am very interested in this topic and he made me hate it. Sitting through his classes is the worst experience ever. He speaks incredibly slowly and in a monotone voice and does absolutely nothing for his students. Never goes over tests. AVOID!!!!!!!!

There was a lot of talk about neurotransmitters and whatnot, which I wasn't prepared for and his monotone voice made lectures kind of painful to sit through; however,if you study the powerpoints he posts on carmen, you will do well in the class. Also, if you do well on the first two exams, you are done for the quarter!

Definitely a lot harder then it seems. A lot of memorizing technical drug names and history of drug use. Tricky test questions and a TON of material to learn. Does not give +/- only A,B,C,D. Test averages in my class were low 70%. It's also really hard to listen to his voice during class and he goes really quick through the slides. AVOID!!
This class should be taught online. There is no reason to go to class. All he does is read directly from the slides. His exams are hard... but his curve in the end is nice. Lectures are VERY boring!

Interesting material. DO NOT BUY BOOK!! You will never open it. His powerpoints come straight from book and test question come straight from powerpoints. Class becomes a bit boring after awhile. Best 2 out of 3 on your test grades. Failry hard class. I still recommend it.

He LITERALLY reads right from the powerpoint slides, so if it's in outline form, don't expect him to make clear sentences and explain further then what is stated on the slide. slides posted online, study from those. grade is based off 2 out of 3 tests. You drop your lowest test. easy if you study the slides that he tells you to for the tests.

Another class where the only grades are a 50% midterm and a 50% final. I hate that. I don't think there was any curve so if you moderately screw one up, well, you are kinda just screwed in general. He seems like a nice guy but after a week you will probably get bored of his lectures and just stop going. Just download/study from the powerpoints.
So disappointed. He is so unclear and the tests are hard!
Has no clue what she's doing. She spends more time correcting her mistakes and rushing through material than actually explaining the material. A straight Stats class would be more helpful.
Terrible. Her lectures and notes drag on forever. The TA was awful as his e-mails and exams were riddled with poor grammar and contradictions. This class was a complete waste of time.

This class was bad, I had to drop it! The information is sooo boring and Dr.  was a very stiff teacher. I felt like he wasn't approachable at all. He told us to refer all questions to the TA! Tests are soo hard. Only good thing about the class was the optional surveys or paper for 50 points extra credit. Dont take unless life depends on it.

Dr.  is a hard teacher. I would not recommend him. When he asks questions in class and students answer the question wrong he puts them down and makes them feel dumb. He does offer extra credit though, and the homeworks are not that hard. Watch out for the tests they can be killers.
He is kind of arrogant and extremely boring- class not recommended.

Heavy weighted classes. Would not recommend anyone to take her classes. They're boring as is her teaching style and personality. I took two of her classes. She's only there for her research funding. Snobby too, with no reason to be.

Had for Poly Sci 101 & 512. Unprofessional. Class time was half spent discussing readings that had nothing to do with the lecture which followed. Did not use Carmen. Found these classes unchallenging and came out with the same knowledge I had going in. Text books were not wisely chosen.

Do not take 3780! They "teach" you with YouTube videos that are all four years out of date! Recitation is basically just graduate students trying to help you with all the problems you'll inevitably encounter, again, because they don't teach you! The videos weren't even made for this course, they're recycled from another! BEYOND LAZY!

Lectures are actually really interesting and well put together, but he is pretty arrogant (though funny sometimes). Tests are VERY hard and totally unrealistic. TA said there were a lot of grad school questions on midterm. HAVE to do reading to know what the tests are talking about. I wouldn't take him again, just because tests are impossible.
was pretty arrogant. His lectures could be fairly entertaining but he was constantly unclear as to what was required.

she was horrible! during office hours she made her students feel stupid for asking questions. isn't that what office hours are for? she thinks she's better than everyone and gives you a bad grade if you can't read her mind. DO NOT take class with her. i always get A's in psych... it's my major.I got a C in her class!

One of the worst professors I have ever had. I do not doubt she is intelligent however her job is to teach... and at this I give her an F. She seems arrogant and god forbid you miss a class... she is not helpful. I found her rather rude.DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS WITH HER.

Never know what is going to be on exams - there have been times I've tried to look up questions after the test and either couldn't find them at all in the lecture notes or text, or they came from chapters not even covered yet.. Also a rather rude/superior attitude..

Took this class as a GE and honestly, worst decision of my life. Professor is absolute, GARBAGE. She said all semester, I will give opportunities to participate in research for extra credit, AND SHE NEVER DID. She also clearly stated in the syllabus, and in emails too, that she would give ONE MINUTE PER QUESTION ON QUIZZES, which NEVER happened.
She is one my my least favorite teachers I have probably had. Her attitude is always negative and is not helpful at all.
Professor  is extremely intelligent and very knowledgable about her field. If you attend lecture and do the required readings this class is a cakewalk. It doesn't hurt that she's good looking.

This guy is in need of an honest review. No doubt, he is a great lecturer but he is never available. I'm pretty sure his office hours don't meet the university's minimum requirements. The class structure is inherently flawed as it is only out of 80 points. His mult. choice questions aren't hard, they're merely convoluted. Most over rated professor.

Try to avoid this professor at all costs. Lectures everyday, at least 50 pages of reading per night from the textbook. VERY difficult grader. Be prepared to be yelled at A LOT. She gets very upset when students do not understand the subjects at the level she does. If you haven't already look her up! She doesn't care about her students whatsoever.

As long as you do the readings from the textbook you will receive an 'A'. My only complaint is that she will go off on liberal tangents and went as far as to say, "Why don't white people just shut up!" as if to say white people didn't have grounds to talk about minority issues.

I took this class with  Harvey during my freshman year at Ohio State. Even now as a senior, it still stands out in my head as the worst experience I've had at OSU and is also by far the worst grade I have ever received in college. She's an unfair grader and a poor lecturer. Look at her Arizona State listing for more information.

i loved this class,  worked so hard to pull it together. she put a lot of pressure on us, and sometimes it was really frustrating, like she needed a chill pill, but well worth it, and i totally respect her for it.

If you can avoid professor , DO IT. A ridiculous amount of work for no reason. Extremely harsh grader. I was literally.5% away from an A and she refused to offer anything. Which isn't the end of the world, but overall her class just feels like a bunch of busy work and like she takes off points just cause she feels like it.

I did not care for Professor  one bit. She didnt really seem to know what she was talking about. She was quite ditzy at times and laughed at the mistakes that she made often.She assigns too much reading for the amount of assignments she expects you to do.
Takes TopHat attendance (ends up being 15% of grade); uploads lectures online, but in a very confusing manner; exams are impossible as he asks for minute details briefly mentioned in slides.

Professor 's lectures might be the cure to narcolepsy. He definitely knows his material but has no idea how to convey it. His notes are filled with acronyms that you will have no idea what they stand for when you go to prepare for his exams. He also uses terms that he does not go over and assumes you know what he's talking about.

Worst polisci class I have taken at OSU. Like every1 says on here, multiple choice exams in which 1 word makes the difference if you get the ? right. Lectures, textbook, and online notes, are not helpful. attendance is a part of your grade (you will be board). If it was not for the curve, many students would end up with D's and F's. AVOID HIM!!!!!!

Worst class I have ever taken. Clearly knows his stuff,but can't communicate that with the average student. He's also a law school prof and teaches the class like we're all about to pass the bar tomorrow. To pass an exam is to have an angel on your side. Do yourself a favor and pick a different class, or drop while you still have time.

As an aspiring law student, his tests are multiple choice and extremely unpractical. Exams are on Carmen, which tends to glitch and mess up your answers. It gives you no room to make your case like an actual law exam. He uses this STUPID attendance taking software called Tophat that you'll waste $20 on. Don't waste time. Find a better class.

Terrible professor in a sense that he is VERY BORING. Exams are open booknotes, but WATCH OUT ! He'll put a lot of questions with: A,B,C,D, All of the above, none of the above, BC, AD? the answers will sometimes come down to a single word that makes the difference. Unless you plan on going to law school, there is no benefit in taking this course.
Useful class but so boring you'll want to die. Tests are HARD despite being open book. Prof's notes are posted online but are extremely disorganized. Final exam looked nothing like the midterm.
AVOID AT ALL COSTS. This guy is HORRIBLE. No interest in teaching whatsoever, exams are horrible...AVOID.

Extremely nice professor and very helpful...bring a pillow to class because his lectures are very boring. Seems very interested in the topics covered but he's the opposite when it comes to teaching...open book/note tests

Was late to the majority of classes and was not prepared most of the time. Was aggressive to students in lecture and email who had issues understanding concepts. His clothes were sometimes dirty and his butt hung out. He also had poor hygiene. He took a long time to grade and return emails. I learned nothing from the class

I didn't like this class, or him as a teacher. VERY UNPROFESSIONAL. Walks in late every day, wears wife beaters and jeans (eew!), takes weeks to hand back papers and exams, lectures straight from powerpoint, takes forever to answer emails... His comments on papers and exams are completely illegible, and thus useless. Take another writing class!

She could have given me 1 extra point on an essay, but instead decided to stop me from graduating because of ONE POINT. I lost my job teaching at OSU, lost my admissions to graduate school, and was forced to take out an extra loan... over ONE point.

Dr.  is smart, presents the material in an interesting and straight forward manner and extremely helpful to her class. In addition, she is STUNNINGLY BEAUTIFUL, has a great sense of humor and is apparently a huge sports fan. Being in her class was quite possibly the best classroom experience of my college career. WOW, is all I can say.

She cares that her students learn, but she doesnt respect them. No technology during class and no chance of recovery after midterm. Exams are hard because she makes the vocabulary on the multiple choice test your IQ not your knowledge of the course. If you dont go to class and participate every day and read every reading, dont expect an A.

Even though the class was super easy, especially with all the extra credit, I hated every single minute of it. She's a boring lecturer and goes on and on about the easiest and most self explanatory concepts.
I relied solely on the lectures and pulled an A-. She just got her master's, but she is a really good teacher. Very hot too!

I literally learned nothing in this class and would not recommend it. You can probably pick a class thats easy and youll actually learn in. Took a post test (not for a grade) at the end and knew as much as when I started. But, hes nice guy and labs are extremely easy. Weeklyish write ups on interesting articles are graded for completion.

Check out his CV. He is great at self-promotion. If you deal with him you will find out at some point that he is really only interested in himself. He does very little fieldwork or lab work but he gets all the publications. He lets other folks do the work and he gets the credit. That's how it works. Enjoy.

Worst professor I've experience thus far. Unhelpful, condescending, and worst of all, he based his class on 3 exams. After taking the exams, I felt I couldn't have studied any more in order to understand the material, simply because he figures that we should already know half of the material from other classes! Terrible. Just...don't do it.

is a very poor and unclear professor, his lecture slides are terrible, he jumps around way too much and his exams are unfairly hard. If you are not a science major with a strong genetics background run and hide, this class is waaaayyyy too hard for a GEC and I have a 3.9 in my honors major.
What is Cultural Marxisim  ? Do you think you can answer that without changing the subject or direction? Don't get philosophical on my butt!

Incredibly boring instructor. Feels like a self help section more than a university level class. It's not difficult so long as you keep up with class material, but doing so feels like a chore. No textbook, readings online (and all more interesting than the lectures), but you do have to pay $10 for a folder full of useless charts. Do not take!

one of the worst teachers I've had- incredibly confusing & boring. Makes it ten times harder than it has to be. 3 exams and weekly homework are the only grades. too many questions on the exam for the time given and asks you to calculate things he gave you in hw examples so you have no idea how to do it. SPSS is hard to get at first but gets better

This class is useless for research and Dr.  is more worried about how to make figures look a certain way than teaching the class about the data that make the figure. This course hasn't changed in several years and it is clearly missing the mark for what graduate students need.

Do NOT take this class. He's rude, refuses to answer most questions--when he does it's in an unhelpful manner. He does not explain things well either. On the tests the questions ask for things that are different from what he wants, you have to be practically psychic to pass. The grading is unfair and sporadic. Worst class ever.

RIDICULOUS! Unless you love SAS do NOT take this class. The program apparently can't be put on Macs or Vista, so you're basically screwed. He's completely unfair, and rude. This was the worst class I have ever taken!

He avoided answering questions and was generally disrespectful. He did a terrible job explaining SAS and took off points on the homework for things not even specified on the assignment. The textbook was TERRIBLE and so hard to understand. I got a 95 on the first midterm and a 54 on the second midterm so watch out. The final wasnt bad.

Materials laid out in a digestible format, major concepts clearly outlined. Long boring unhelpful lectures. Most learning happens out of class. Questions usually met with disdain, he gets defensive/mean/weird if you are confused? Get ready to work hard. Extra credit for going to lecture, open book quizzes, collaborative homework's, and tough exams.

Worst professor Ive ever had in the psych department (my major). Had a test average of 50% for almost every exam and would yell at us for being dumb and incompetent. Lectures make absolutely no sense. Got defensive and weird when asked questions. 15 of students in the groupme voted that they were failing the class the day before the final.

Most boring lecturer ever. Super hard grader. Takes off points for almost no reason and then will not discuss it with the student. The class consists of 3 total grades. He doesn't respond to emails or takes forever to respond. Most of the exam answers were found in the readings that are posted. Take this if you want to hurt your GPA.

Lazy opinion based rants with little objective fact and no dialogue.
 
 Rants include: "Why we should allow child s** dolls for pedophiles," "Why cars should be abolished," and "Why Apple is not innovative."
 
 If you want to learn anthropology, buy a textbook and form your own based opinion. I love anthropology, but this class was so disappointing.

Guy was a complete tool. Lectures felt like they went on for an eternity, full of cool little zingers that Im sure  thinks are mad clever, guaranteed to make your eyes roll so fast into your head that you'll fall out of your chair. Basically stopped showing up to class, still did fine but don't recommend if you can avoid him.

Worst professor I have had at this school yet and for a GENERAL EDUCATION CLASS. He is grossly ignorant and operates on his own schedule. Had covid at the beginning of the semester and had to email him 4 times before I received the content I missed. Words his questions unfairly that answers are opinion based but he does not agree with anyone.

AVOID AT ALL COSTS!!! This class had unneeded stress. He is pretentious yet ill-informed. I think they thought he was smart based on his accent but he scammed them. He made up rubrics after the fact and left little feedback that is unhelpful and seems to not make sense. He definitely skimmed them. Highest grades on the two main papers were low A's

is an incompetent wanking mess. If his unbelievable pretentiousness doesn't turn you off then the outrageous grading system and constant yawning probably will. Will not reply to emails from students despite the lack of a TA, has only remedial knowledge of the subject being taught. Overall a huge waste of time.

Grossly incompetent, what more is there to say? Takes the class way too seriously, grades off an imaginary rubric of what he likes or doesn't. Pretentious, and I had difficulty writing the way he liked even though I have been told I have been the best writer in classes before and took a writing class at the same time where I had a high A.

He seems to be nice but he is a terrible professor. The lectures are interesting, but unhelpful. He does not treat it like the throwaway, participation grade class he should treat it as. The rubrics are vague and has lengthy grading making feedback unhelpful. Grades are harsh and illogical. He doesn't know good writing. He should change or be fired

I'm in this class right now. Lots of complaints: The worst lecturer I've ever had. Doesn't seem like he knows the content he's trying to teach, just stands behind the computer screen and mumbles off his notes, looking down the entire time. Absolutely no class discussions. Exam was nothing he said it would be and much of it he never discussed.

DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS IF YOU CAN. There is essentially no grading criteria, and even if you follow assignment guidelines perfectly, he will find ways to lower your grade. One of the best gpa droppers out there.
She is incredibly frustrating to listen to - she tends to stutter and ramble a lot. Ridiculous amount of reading assigned, and her grading is tough despite unclear expectations. Not recommended.

Wow where do I start, took an online race in America class, the work is absolutely ridiculous for it being a 3000 level class. Its way tooo much reading he nitpicks everything on each of your assignments, if you dont add a word count on your assignments which are 6 total due every Wednesday and Friday you will lose all points. RUN RUN RUN AWAY

This class is an actual joke in terms of difficulty.  himself isn't a native English speaker so he pretty much gives everyone 100% on all assignments as long as they are turned in. While his lectures are fairly interesting and intuitive, the homework for this class is high school level. Enroll in this class for an easy break.

He can be pretty crass when leaving feedback on your assignments, especially essays. In my opinion, he lets his leftist bias show while teaching the class. For example, he asked us to asses where racial tension was in the U.S, but when he graded it he acted like there was only one right answer. There are many other examples of his leftist bias.

This was a great class! You watch documentaries that cover many social issues that are very interesting. His accent did frighten me at first because I have had difficulty understanding him during the first two lectures but I grew used to it and he uses his experiences coming from a Latin American family which helps relay the material.

English is not his first language; has an accent but you get used to it. good teacher. Youll read a lot (20 page essays per week andthen write summary). Attendance is basically mandatory although you are allowed to miss a few classes. Tests are easy essays. This class was one of my favorites. learned a lot. Heated debates! never used the textbook

Do not take his classes. The class material could be incredibly easy to understand, and he tries to make it sound more complicated to suit his ego. His tests are unnecessarily difficult and I feel like he does it on purpose. He doesn't get enough love from his department so he takes it out on the students. Stay away from him.

"Chip" may be the worst professor at Ohio State. He is so condescending and full of himself and made the class harder and more boring than it ever needed to be. I looked up his rating before I took the class and he seemed okay but trust me he is not. I hated every second I spent in this class and was beyond glad to see the last of him.

"Chip" is resentful his research can't earn grants and takes it out on students by taking a entry level class full of athletes and people who are just trying to get into the major way to seriously. He makes things unnecessarily difficult and believes he is the "cool" teacher but is unhelpful and screws students over on exams and quizzes. Avoid him!

"Chip" is pessimistic and not helpful when it comes to students individually. Lecture notes are ridiculous (grammar, length) and he doesn't have the ability to clarify. He puts most of his work on his TA's and will ramble during lecture- hard to focus. The class is too large for him to care.CERTAINLY made this course more difficult than needed
Good luck passing this class. Averages on the exams are D's. Hardest class I've ever taken and he makes his tests unpassable. Do not take this course!!!
Not difficult but not particularly interesting. Seems generally nice but came off as very condescending in emails and one-ones.
A nice enough professor, but not very engaging and often comes across as condescending
I hated her class. Very boring, and she failed me by .5 points and would not do anything about. She makes people do expeirments that dont count for anything. This class was just plain stupid to take.
Very easy on the eyes
She seemed to be confused about what she was talking about at times, and she spoke in the same bored tone the entire lecture. Take a different professor!

Dr.  was young, and it showed. While her class wasn't too bad, and she did a good job or giving a lot of examples, I got the vibe that her lectures were really disorganized and some of the assignments were really unclear about what she wanted on them. Not a terribly difficult class, if you have to take 549, take it with her..not bad to look at

Horrible professor. Teaches with powerpoint and goes WAY too fast to write anything down so make sure you print off the notes.So, if you learn better by writing things down you're screwed. Exams are very difficult for no reason. Must read every page in the book to do well on an exam. Thinks he's fuuny, but isn't.

Papers were easy to write. Reading is boring, but do it. The tests are impossible because it is filled with so many tricks and lures. Even if you go to class, its still hard to get higher then a B with the curve. I would recommend it. the class is interesting. alot of info to be absorbed.  is a good professor.

Going to class helps out a lot and a lot of questions are from the textbook and not discussed in class. He is very clear in lecture on what he expects. On the two short essays, follow EXACTLY. If you deviate or try to go "above and beyond" he will FAIL YOU!
sucks. get another professor if you can. his tests are way too hard. it's like he enjoys watching you suffer through the exams. don't say i didn't warn you.

he talks way too fast and he likes to make his tests ridiculously hard.. like to the point where it's just unnecessary. READ YOUR BOOK; he likes to screw you over with questions from the readings. don't memorize definitions, but be able to understand the concepts and how they're applied. attendance isn't mandatory since he puts slides on carmen.

Dr.  is not patient or inviting when it comes to students questions. She responds in quite a defensive and irritated manner. She is also very contradictory. She says she is not trying to trick you and writes her tests/assignments in a very technical way.

This class is ok.  was rarely on time, impossible to reach, and overall disorganized. I only got an A in the class because of all the extra credit (4 pts for SEIS, and 4 pts for attendance). I didn't learn anything, which made writing a 12-page research paper difficult. The TAs grade them though so you'll get an A even if your paper is awful

I learned shockingly little new information in class. Like, shockingly. Readings were helpful occasionally, but Dr.  spent most of his time in lectures rewording his slides so it sounded like he wasn't just reading from them. So not bad information necessarily, just horrendously, horrendously boring.

He is very boring and the lecture is just what's on the sides, there really isn't reason to go to class especially since the TA does all the grading and comments. Also the exams are very short. 3 ID terms and 2 essays, missing one brings the exam down, and with only 3 grades , midterm, final, and paper its do or die. Avoid this class and teacher!

Terrible. Avoid at all costs this class is basically self-taught. You have to read chapters from a textbook since the test is over all of it, but he spends each lecture on around 2 pages. Lecture is WORTHLESS and his lecture really just feel like an old man rambling on without clear idea of what he wants to get across. DO NOT TAKE IF U CAN

AVOID! (grad and undergrad). This class was incredibly frustrating. Read the book or you will not get above a C (that is as low as he goes at least). Lectures consisted of nothing but boosting his own ego & showing clips of "moral exemplars" and "What Would You Do?". Only grades are a paper, presentation, 3 exams, and "discussion Qs" NOT optional.

Dr.  is one of the most kind and caring professors I've had at OSU. He does not use lecture slides, which is an adjustment at first, but is very engaging in class. His course was no cakewalk and the material bordered on dull at times, but it wasn't bad if you pay attention and study for exams.

Dr.  is one of the best professors at OSU. Truly one of the nicest, most knowledgeable, and helpful professors I've had. Not an easy A but wont make you cry yourself to sleep. Not an overwhelming amount of work but covers a lot of material. He does not use any notes and lecture is completely oral, which is an adjustment but helped me focus.

is one of my favorite professors at OSU because he cares a lot about his students. I learned a lot in this course, and not just surface-level content but a deeper understanding of the Supreme Court. I recommend recording lectures because while they are engaging, they are long, and they are pretty much your only source of class content.

Professor 's class isn't "easy" but you will learn a lot. I truly feel lucky to have been able to take 2 classes with him. You won't meet a professor at OSU that's more knowledgeable, kind, and caring. And he's hilarious.

He does not use any kind of slides or another presentation tool in class, he talks at you for 1:20 straight. This class was also graded solely on exams, which is not something I enjoy. I found recording the lectures to be somewhat helpful, but overall was not a fan of him at all. He is also confusing, sometimes going back on what he said before.

Professor  was likely the most knowledgable and accessible professor I've had. The class was comprised of 3 papers, all research-based. However, you're given the time and resources to get it done, and he is there every step of the way to help. I wish I had another class with him because he is one of the kindest and smartest professors I've had.

might be the best professor I've had at OSU. While the class is totally lecture based, the way he presents the material is so interesting and you can tell how much he knows and loves what he does. I would suggest studying early because if you do the topic guides and know them well, you'll be fine on the exams!

He's a great professor. The lectures are dull and sooooo long, and you'll definitely fall asleep. He really knows what he's talking about, though, and you really have no excuse for not doing well if you show up. Lots of readings, but skimming them is more than enough.
Great teacher

Mr. is a great teacher who knows his stuff. He is liberal(check fec.gov for who he's donated to) but does a great job hiding it. DO THE READINGS.the exams are multiple choice/essay. he gives the possible 6 essay questions in advance. My advice would be to draft the essays out in advance after doing readings,so that you're not doing the night B4

Amazing professor! Creates a great balance between professionalism and fun (humor) in the classroom. Material is very relevant to current affairs. He's always very accessible, and is always willing to help. He's a Prof. Emeritus, so take a class with him while he's still at the University!

Dr.  is extremely passionate about the field of Political Science and is very knowledgable about the subject matter. Yes he does tend to stray off topic, but the majority of his lectures are interesting and informative. He references the books and they are extremely helpful to study for the midterms with.
Professor  is incredibly well knowledge and generally a nice person. I highly recommend him.

Really great professor, one of the best I've ever had. Very friendly and communicates really well with the students. The class wasn't too challenging but wasn't easy, and I learned a lot. Highly recommended.

Awesome guy. Class is easy and he really knows his stuff. Always gives you room to voice your opinion, and grades you not on your opinion, but how you back it up and how well you know the material. Exams are straightforward and simple and he puts in a lot of cool stories and opinion pieces in his lectures. Definitely recommend him.

Prof  is a really great teacher. Helpful with anything you could ever need help with. Instant responses to emails, go out of his way for office hours etc. Lecture can be boring at times, but a lot of political anecdotes. Paper is fairly easy and exams are straight forward. Gives you essays ahead of time to study.

Great teacher. Clearly knew the topic, researched any questions he did not know the answer to. Grades very fairly, the essay was easy to get a good grade on. Attendance not required, but can be used to bump grade up if you are close. Overall great teacher, if you have the option, take him!
Professor  is a good guy. His class is easy, but you learn a lot. I thought the material was interesting - and you could see that he enjoyed teaching it.

Dean  is a good teacher. He is very informative and does a great job relating the topics to more recent elections. The class can get boring at times, but it is very interesting. The class is not too difficult and the paper topic is very interesting.
very nice and interesting! Explains everything clearly
Very nice man, interesting class; genuinely decent human being and very bright man.
No Comments
Great sense of humor.
No Comments

I enjoyed this class. He posts slides on carmen, but does add more informations during lecture. While lecture is not mandatory, I would recommend attending for the extra information. He has lots of stories that relates with the material. The test are from both lecture and books. It's not a bad class to take and has a nice curve.

I really enjoyed this class. Dr.  is a little disorganized but his lectures are interesting. His tests are from both the book and the lecture material and he loves testing on statistics. If you're interested in psychopathology you'll like the class. I recommend it.

His statistics are a lot of times way off but you need to know them for the exams anyways. You can get an A fairly easily if you read the book and attend class....but if you are really interested in Psychology- his class is frustrating because lecture doesn't relate to Adjustment at all.

Dr.  is a very nice guy who is interested in his field BUT I would caution you not to take the class. He uses outdated materials and information. If you choose to take the course make sure that you read the textbook cover to cover and write down every random statistic he says in class.

This class is not as bad as it may seem. He is a practicing psychologist so he lectures on what he thinks is interesting and then you are responsible for what is in the book for the exam. He loves statistics so pay close attention to them while your taking book notes. He also gives a pretty big curve which helps a lot. I got an A fairly easily.

Dr.  is really nice but I would caution everyone interested in taking his Psych 681 course. First, he lectures little to nothing from the book and you are responsible for the book and lectures on the tests (they're often opposing information). He is spacey, extremely unorganized, his tests don't make sense, & has lectured incorrect information.

The class was interesting and he was a pretty good lecturer. A lot of people didn't come to class but if you go to lecture and read the book thoroughly it is easy to get an A. He doesn't cover the reading in class so you have to be motivated to do it on your own. He seemed like a really nice guy and had a lot of good stories from his clinical work.

He makes mistakes on his own exams, makes you choose between what he says in class and what the book says, and if that's not enough, you spend half the time trying to figure out what the questions are asking. Nice guy, but extremely spacey, making for an unreliable professor.

Dr.  is obviously a caring man, but he is just not the best teacher. The class was unorganized and it was hard to get questions answered. You must read the book very closely! and the topics assigned for reading will be different than that discussed in lecture. The class is so frustrating it's not worth taking even if you're highly interested.

I just recently graduated from OSU and this was one of my favorite classes...and it was even in the early morning. Dr.  had some really interesting things to say and if you went to class, he gave hints for the tests. Very intelligent, educated and fair prof. Hightly recommended!
I like the guy but the test are tough.

This was my first class as a non-trad student after being out of school for 8 years. I found Dr. 's lectures interesting and relevant to the real world. He uses a lot of stories which were interesting to me. Half of the tests are from the text, so there is a lot of reading involved. If you go to class and read the text, you can get an A.

Attendence is not mandatory but I would definitely recommend going, since part of the exams come from the book. Dr.  is an amazing professor. He knows his material and is very passionate about all of it. Lectures were very interesting. I don't get up for many 9 am classes, but I hardly ever missed his!
No Comments

This is a must to take psych class!! Dr.  makes an hour and 48 min seem like half an hour. His lectures are outstanding, applicable to real world, nothing obscure. But careful!His tests have a lot of stats and are long. Even so, its a well balanced class and very informative and entertaining. Overall is great, study and you can easily get an A.

Dr.  is an excellent professor. He really cares about his student's success. His course is very well-organized and he does as much as he can to make a course of this difficulty accessible to his students. The only note was some of the readings were really long, over 100 pages, and could have easily been assigned with only the abstract.

Overall solid professor. Class can seem a bit slow at times and he isn't the best with powerpoint, but he certainly knows his stuff. If you attend class, pay attention, and do the in class writings, it's hard to get a bad grade. Exams are easy, and he look like Tobias from Arrested Development without a mustache. Solid dude

I actually enjoyed this class with Professor . His exams are pretty easy as long as you read the chapters and attend class. Complete the critical thinking questions and it is hard to get a bad grade in this class. He knows what he's talking about and invites you on jail visits with his higher level classes! I'd take a class with him again

He is unresponsive to e-mails if you need to miss class, so you don't even know if he received them. He doesn't give out study guides. He says read the chapters assigned & study the slides which are like 80 slides. He doesn't post the ppts before hand so you give up taking notes. He says you can arrange to change your final if needed but doesn't.

Dr.  is a very nice professor and really wants students to do well-- she even brought snacks to lecture for students multiple times! Her exams are almost exactly the same questions as her quizzes, so make sure to review those often. There is a weekly online quiz but otherwise exams are just quizzes and exact lecture slides. Not a bad class!

Group work is terrible, but Dr.  makes it bearable! This class was very challenging, but Dr.  was there to support us every step of the way. He gives wonderful feedback, and his great sense of humor helps numb the pain when that feedback is negative. He's quite literally an award-winning instructor, so take his classes!

I'm writing this to those of you who attend the first day of class and think, "Wow, this guy sounds so annoying." I thought the same thing on the first day, but I was quickly humbled.  is the funniest professor I've had at OSU and he can thoroughly relate the content to the students. He actually teaches and I felt prepared for every exam.
Absolutely loved   as a professor. Literally, the best professor I've ever had hands down. His exams can be vigorous but his class is an absolute must-take, a professor I will never forget.

Dr.  is one of the best professors I have had at OSU. Funny, engaging, and eccentric. Cheat sheets for exams, but make sure you go to class and pay moderate attention because the slides are not self-explanatory.

He's an eccentric and funny guy with excellent music taste. Initially, I was intimidated and scared for my wellbeing in this class, but because he's very good at explaining and teaching, I ended up doing very well. He also gives good feedback if you meet with him during office hours.

Super interesting and eccentric guy. His voice is really funny to listen to. Explains the materials very clearly and tries to answer questions all the time. Even though data analysis seems like a dull class he actually makes it a lot more engaging. Would recommend taking any of his classes.

I really enjoyed this class, and though I may not have always understood the material, Dr.  was more than willing to help with any questions I had. He may talk incredibly fast but I guess he's just excited about the material. Also, he might be a stand up comedian in his spare time (need confirmation on this)

11/10 My favorite professor EVER. I hate college, but looked forward to his class every day. He wants students to succeed, actually learn, and treats you like a colleague. His assignments were fun to do (I know, it sounds like a reach,) exams are fair (plus cheat sheet!,) and lectures are top tier. TAKE HIS CLASS TAKE HIS CLASS TAKE HIS CLASS!!!
Literally the best professor I've ever had. He's super funny and it's easy to get an A in the class if you do the homework and pay a moderate amount of attention. Couldn't recommend him more.

A very funny professor who always asks us to "bombard" him with questions and is very quick to respond to emails. He provides full and short lectures on each chapter and puts an emphasis on individual exploration. We had a weekly quiz, discussion posts, questions, journal entry/ activity, and a quiz make-up activity with no exams or tests.

professor  is soo funny and makes sure that he is available for students whenever they need. it's very clear that he genuinely cares about teaching and his students. the course load is heavy and confusing at times but very interesting. if you're confused about something, he provides great explanations and will clear things up. def recommend

Super funny guy. Lectures aren't mandatory but are never boring - I would recommend attending but he posts abbreviated recorded lectures that are super helpful as well. His tests can be a bit difficult, though - it's sometimes hard to tell exactly what you need to know versus what is extra information. Regardless, he's wildly entertaining.

I love Doctor . He is kind but also extremely hilarious in his classes. His mixture of self-deprecation as well as his beautifully crafted power points make him my favorite professor I have had yet. Though the lectures are not attendance-mandatory, you don't want to miss them (especially for his random tangents).

For Halloween, he dressed up as Steve from Blue's Clues and all of us collectively spent the lecture trying to figure out if he was in costume or not, because it wasn't far from how he dresses daily.
 
 11/10 would attend a lecture of his about paint drying.

I don't do rate my professors, but he deserves an awesome rating. The funniest professor and one who cares about his students. He's always asking us for questions and when we ask them he is so happy to answer them. I hope he stays as a professor for a long time because he can make learning fun.

Dr.  is an amazing professor!! I took another one of his course in AU 2021 and I absolutely loved it. Dr.  is amazing at lecturing and he has a way of making sure that you remember the material being taught. Although the exams can be challenging, he is always open to help during his office hours. Definitely recommend!!

Professor  is a very swell guy. I would say lectures are mandatory if you want to have success in this class, especially if you do not have a background in data. I did not know much going in, but I feel pretty confident moving forward because of this course. It's not easy material but I feel lucky I had Dr  to help.

This was by far my favorite class this semester. Dr.  is super engaged in the teaching material, funny and has high standards for students. Homework, projects and exams were challenging but fair, and I learned a lot from them (they did not feel like mindless busy work). 100% recommend this class and Dr. .

Dr.  is extremely knowledgeable in the topics he teaches and is very generous with extra credit opportunities. The course itself is test heavy (4 exams) but his are not cumulative and they're over less than 5 subjects each.  is very enthusiastic and encourages students to ask questions to make sure they understand the material!

Not a very engaging professor, but the class is easy. Powerpoints are straight from the book and tests are straight froom the powerpoints..do not buy book! You can find it at the library reserves. Only 3 tests, with the lowest dropped. Grades are curved at the end..interesting material!
A very good professor - I really enjoyed attending his lectures. He's extremely knowledgeable on this subject and is genuinely interested in teaching. Awesome prof, awesome class!

The material is tough, but if you pay CLOSE attention during lecture you should do okay. I'm into this topic so it was probably a bit more interesting for me. He's kind of witty, explains things pretty well for such a complex topic.
very interesting, lot of material, grades are curved
Great class--great prof

This class should be named Into to Neuropharmacology. Avoid if you are dumb about Psychiatry and drugs. You'll be memorizing pill names and what receptors they hit. I got a B by looking at the powerpoints the night before. that's only because of my previous intrest in crazy meds. Tough class for most, although heavily curved.
Best class ever.
Great professor, got me interested in this topic and now I'm going to graduate school!
Totally awesome class. Best professor I ever had.

He wasn't the most well organized prof, but lectures are interesting and he fosters discussion very well. Tests were difficult, if you didn't study. He is very willing to help, but you have to ask for it first! Just because you didn't study and didn't get an A doesn't make it a bad class or him a bad prof.
Watch out for this guy. He only does 2 grades - a midterm and final - but they're so hard! The class was called psychology of drugs and behavior, yet I have not seen any behavior aspects yet.
I LOVED this professor. She extremely helpful with any questions you may have, and she really cares for her students. She is AWESOME!

Dr.  is absolutely amazing. She is friendly and funny and I actually enjoyed lectures. Material isn't hard to deal with and there's no textbook, 3 exams worth 60pts each and a couple small assignments. I had her for Psych 300 as well, I'd recommend her for any class. She's caring, considerate, and understanding. I can't say enough. She's great
Dr.  is the one of the nicest professors I've ever had. I would take her again if i could...her TA Hye Bin is a tough grader though. 300 is an easy class, an easy A.
Dr.  is the one of the nicest professors I've ever had. I would take her again if i could...he TA Hye Bin is a tough grader though. 300 is an easy class, an easy A.

Good teacher, great person. Willing to go above and beyond to help students. Left me a note on my homework asking if I wanted any advice on applying to graduate schools, without me asking her beforehand.

Dr.  is SUCH a nice lady!! This class is tough though, and there is no book, so you pretty much just have your lecture slides and notes to go by. I would recommend attending lecture even though the subject matter can be very dry. Study hard and you'll do fine. I really recommend this class to psych students who want to go to grad school!

Dr.  is ALWAYS there to help and will work with you if you ask her to. She does make semi-frequent mistakes on her powerpoint slides etc. but if you are confused she will clear the confusion for you. Class is hard but if you need help ASK and you will be fine.

If you go to class and pay attention, I don't see how you could not do well. Though i did not personally find the subject matter to be interesting, class was bearable and attendance (while not mandatory) will really help you, because a lot of what is said in class is helpful in understanding and learning the material, and is included on the exams.

Class dragged on a little but  made it fun. Grade is determined from 3 hw short hw assignments, a survey, 2 midterms, and a comprehensive final. I didn't look at the book once and I got a B+ in the class. Print out the notes, go to lecture, and you will have no problem. Also, her TA is a very sweet girl who is very helpful.

Dr.  is cool! I picked up this class last minute after dropping something else and I'm really glad I did because it was not only surprisingly interesting but personally enriching (you get to take career and personality tests). She's really clear and helpful too and has an amusing dry humor. I would take anything else she teaches.
Dr.  is awesome. She's funny and adorably awkward if I weren't graduating I'd try to take more classes from her. Doesn't make you buy a book either!
Very sweet woman. Extremely helpful. Decently interesting class.
Amazing teacher! Keeps lectures interesting and is so extremely helpful in making sure you understand everything!!!

take your next class with prof !! she's awesome...always ends class 15 mins early, puts all notes up on power point. only 3 homework assignments and 3 exams. the homework was quite easy, and the exams are all 50 mc questions. her wording can be a bit misleading, but if you get less than a B you're an idiot

Extremely lenient on tests, never gave out homework assignments, and very intellectual on the material. The classes were somewhat boring, but if you made an effort, she'd make sure you got a good grade no matter what.

Dr.  is awesome! I only took this class because I knew it was good for grad school prep, but now I love psych testing! I would recomend this class or any of her classes to anyone. She's a great professor and really funny. I always looked forward to her lectures!
I loved this class!
Great job! Learned a lot in this course. The atmosphere was supportive, and discussion topics and presenters were excellent!
exellent teacher. very clear and organized as he managed to make research ethics interesting. very fair grader.

As long as you read the text or go to lecture, the tests are cake. I went to lecture more than half the time, but it wasn't really necessary. He was pretty funny and the lectures were not bad at all. Do the 3 hw assignments just in case you bomb a test. He doesnt curve your grade, so you get what you get. Great professor though.

As many others have stated, not the most exciting material, but not the worst, either. He does try and throw in a few anecdotes (many about his cat or his wife) to try and make the material relevant. But, when he asks questions (during lecture) he will only agree if you give the answer he wants. Overall, not too painful. Notes are posted online

Pretty good teacher. The class itself is pretty boring but it isn't difficult. Going to class def makes it a lot easier. He gives an opportunity for extra credit that can really help your grade if you do it.

No matter who teaches this class it's going to be a boring class. Dr.  tries to make it as interesting as possible. He cracks jokes, and tells interesting stories. It's not too bad. Him and his TA helped me a lot in their office. They will be happy to go over exams with you, and explain anything.

Pretty hard class but totally doable, but like someone else said, it's extremely easy to get the 50 bonus points, and they do matter since your grade is out of 1000. I thought the class was extremely boring, and this is the first class I have ever taken which you could definitely get an A without going to class; Everything you need is online.
Good prof. Clear when explaining course material. Very helpful. Worth taking!

He is by far the most effective teacher I have had. Regardless of the material, he does a really good job explaining. I actually learned everything in class just my listening to him. Really good at explaining things.
Tricky class, make sure you understand his testing style and what he thinks is important. He does give extra credit to help if you didn't do so hot on an exam, but exams aren't easy.
This class wasn't the hardest but it wasnt the easiest...the tests werent too hard but the paper was a pain. The class was soooo boring and i'm suprised I made it as much as I did!
The class is really boring but really easy. Just read the book and the notes and you will be fine on the tests. Can get an easy 50 bonus points which makes getting a good grade even easier.

made lectures very interesting considering the material. homeworks very easy & offers easy extra credit. do need to spend some time studying for exams though. overall really good prof. would take another class with him again.
was not the most exciting guy, but he was very helpful and the class was pretty easy. Just don't take it in the morning, or you will never go to class.

You can tell he's genuinely interested in the stuff he teaches. Unfortunately the material is still very boring. He puts all the notes online so going to class is purely optional and it really won't hurt your grade to skip as long as you read the notes before the midterm

The material is dull, but easy to understand. He gives you the notes online. 50 bonus points if you do some surveys. I thought this class was much easier than psych 100. If I recall correctly something like 75% of the class got C+ or above.
The material was horribly boring, but he actually made in enjoyable. He has a great sense of humor. He gives you every opportunity to do well.
Great teacher! Tests are all essay, but he grades them very fairly. But bring a pillow on presentaion days, that's a bore!
Great professor. She takes her time to explain everything.

Her class was interesting and went by pretty fast. We had plenty class discussions but never put anyone on the spot if they didn't want to contribute. Attendance is important, its worth it anyway. Only one paper, there is a lot of reading for short quizzes, easy to pass them. Exams are mult choice but rather long. Over all I would take her again.

This is my favorite professor so far. She is so wonderful and has an amazing personality. She is always willing to help us. I lov going to each of her classes. She always makes everything so engaging.

She's an amazing professor, gives lots of reading, however she goes over all assigned texts in details during lectures, listens to student input, she is always there to help, always emails back and is polite and professional.
Awesome professor. You put in the time and effort, she will do everything she can to help you succeed.
Great instructor

Wonderful professor - clear, concise, and really good at conveying the the material and making it relative. She will go out of her way to help any student who is putting forth a legitimate effort. I highly recommend her!

Dr.  is an amazing professor! She is very clear on what she teaches and everything on her exams is covered in class. Attend class and make sure to read the readings assigned. Dr. B-Z is very helpful and really makes class enjoyable. This is a definite class to take.
She really enjoys what she teaches helping interest you in the material.
Great professor! Do the readings, pay attention and go to class and you'll do fine! She has real passion for sociology.
Definately Recommend!
One of the best professors I have had the pleasure of being in class with.
Best teacher I've ever had.
Her Sociology of Education class is very enlightening and interesting. She is very enthusiastic about her work and is very encouraging. Read the assigned material and show up to class.

Dr.  is an amazing professor! Make sure you study your notes and READ!!!!! A LARGE majority of your grade is based on reading and class participation..so go to class!! Also, she offers a lot of extra credit. Overall, she makes the class fun and entertaining. Just study your notes, come to class, and read and you will pass. I promise.

Mr. s is tough grader, he gives a 3 papers throughout the semester and a topic and even if you follow the topic he will grade like he is an English professor. He counts and deducts points even if one word is misspelled. He does not give extra credit assignments. He expects perfection right away, instead of teaching how to get there.

Professor s was a very tough grader, he looks for specific answers in his assignments. He assigned multiple quizzes throughout the week and a essay with them every other week. His lectures weren't all that great either. He provides the book readings on blackboard- that was the only plus from his class.

There was a lot of reading but it was not necessary. Could retake most quizzes an unlimited number of times. Directions for papers were sometimes unclear, but she was very good at responding to emails in a timely manner and answered questions well. She is a very easy grader.

Dr.  is a really great professor. Her class was really interesting, interactive, and you can tell she's really passionate about what she does. She's also extremely nice; I was 0.02% away from a solid A in her class and didn't realize you could ask for a bump until the end of the next semester. She bent over backwards and bumped me anyway.

Professor  is a decent professor at OSU Mansfield. She remains unbiased in the politics class, even though her opinion on the matter is clear. She is easy to get along with, and is quite understanding when you must miss a class. However, some of her material is difficult to understand. I often found myself using Google to look up answers.

Pretty good professor. She's very liberal but is pretty good at hiding her bias. Her lectures can be pretty boring. She decided to drop all exams so all there is to do is a final constitutional 'simulation', that is a lot of fun. Easy A and fairly interesting GE.
Gives great feedback and clearly outlines what she's looking for in her assignments. In class, she's able to moderate debate while not showing much bias toward either side.

I loved her class! She gives great feedback and goes above and beyond for her students. I loved how she makes sure everyone is involved in class discussions, but does not call on people if they do not know the answer. She also lets you use a cheat sheet on the midterm, and you get a take-home final. Be sure to pay attention and take good notes.
one o my favorite professors eve!

is an awesome professor, you really learn a lot in her class. If you put in the work, you will get good grades. She offers a lot of help and time if you need it, attending study sessions and asking questions makes the exams and papers easier.
Dr.  is very passionate about Political Science and easily my favorite professor I had while on the Mansfield Campus. Would recommend her classes to anyone!

Very hands on course. She encourages students to be involved and discuss issues during classes. Very helpful if you reach out to her. She also gives bonus points for perfect attendance, and has pretty simple exams. Definitely would take another one of her courses.

I really like her. I think she is tough, but very fair! She makes you think and work for your grade. I found the class to be very interesting. Not a slack off class. I found her to be very helpful answering questions. I would take another of her classes.

Professor  was a pretty good instructor and she kept class fun. The only complaint I have is I don't feel like she did a very good job preparing us for the final. Since there were no exams during the quarter, I didn't really know what to expect of the final. Other than that she was great!

Very smart and funny too! I would take another class with her. She is willing to answer questions. She doesn't assign much work but the work she does assign is interesting. She keeps class fun and wants her students to have a good time while learning. A valuable asset to OSU Mansfield!

Makes class fun by mixing lectures with powerpoints, discussions, and debates. Other than the readings, the only assignments all quarter are participating in one debate, 2 3-5 page papers, and the final which she is considering making take home. She likes to keep things interesting and wants you to have a good time. Definitely worth your time!
I didn't watch any of the lectures. I did 20% of the additional readings and did not read the textbook once. I got an A.

This course is super simple. If you have a basic understanding of the US legal system this should be a breeze. Just weekly assignments, three exams, and one 4-6 page paper. If you just complete all the work you should get an A.

I took this class as an online Diversity GE, and it was very interesting! workload is quite manageable each week as well. One thing I will say that exams make up a large portion of your grade, but those are hardly challenging. Other than that, just weekly discussion posts and 1 paper. Great choice for a GE.
Easy class. Workload consisted of no more than a weekly discussion post. Book is recommended but not necessary for the class. Midterms are online and open book and not too hard.

Class was informative but super easy. You get out what you put into it - the lectures and readings are long and interesting, but you really don't need them to do fine with the weekly work. I probably spent like an hour on class each week, plus a couple hours for the final paper. Would recommend.
There were 2 papers, 2 exams and 2 discussion posts every week. Class was easy, but I learned so much! I enhoyed professor s lectures and attitude.

There was one required final paper and 3 exams. There were 2 disscussion posts every week. All exams were extremely easy and open book/note. Professor  was extremely nice and understanding. I enjoyed listening to her lectures.

Professor  was amazing! She's an attorney, so she's very knowledgeable about the subject matter and it shows how much she cares about it. Her class is low-maintenance, just a couple short discussion posts a week, one paper, and non-cumulative open-note exams. Easy A and she was engaging even in online lectures.
Online class so I didn't interact with her much. However she seemed nice and the class is easy.

is THE MAN. One of my favorite professors here at Ohio State. Truly cares about his students and made the subject super interesting. Tests are challenging but he gives you the essay prompts before the exam.
