MacEachern made quality control way more interesting than expected.

Definitley one of the best classes I have taken at OSU. Professor MacGilvray is very likeable and keeps his lectures engaging. It's easy for me to get bored & distracted in classes but I never was for this one. He also gives constructive feedback on papers and really sets you up to do well on exams.

Don't let the 2xxx level fool you-- this class is tough. You will have to come to class and pay attention to know what's going on. Your grade is 90% exams, but they're fair. If you put the work in, it's not awful.  is a really nice guy , engaging in class, and is always willing to help you out if you're lost.

Funniest teacher I've ever had. This class was also very difficult... Based on three written exams. If you tank one, like I did because of a nasty breakup, you can't fully recover from it. Still, his class was ridiculously entertaining, and I learned a lot. I still frequently reference texts I read in this class. Accessible/ helpful outside class.

He is funny and his lectures were pretty entertaining but sometimes no matter how hard I tried I still had trouble understanding what we were talking about. I think political theory might just be a difficult subject in general. I wish he would have been more clear with what we were supposed to take away from each reading.

I have taken two classes with MacGilvray now and he is TOUGH, there is not argument from there, but it is worth it. Even if you do not fully understand the reading, he goes over it in class knowing full well they are confusing af sometimes. Honestly, going to class for his horrific/hilarious board drawings is just worth it in itself.

Professor MacGilvray is not only an amazing professor but also a great human being. His class is very inspiring and very heavily test-based but he does curve the score to your advantage every time. However you dont have to be worried about the tests as long as your pay attention in class, take careful notes and make flash cards for test studies.

ok, so this class all depends on the students that are in it. Ive heard some really cringey comments in this class. since he offers credit for participation youll have a lot of annoying freshmen trying to kiss his ass. grading is very vague. class isnt easy, but the prof is very likable.

Dr. MacGilvray is amazing, but the class is definitely hard. It's totally worth it, but you have to study, and take really detailed notes during class (look out for buzz words!). His class consists of three exams, each worth 30% of your grade, and 5 pop quizzes (lowest one dropped), for the remaining 10%. He's really funny and intelligent.
He is great. You do a lot of reading but then go over it in class. Hes very engaging and does a lot of funny things to keep it interesting. Great guy.

Most engaging and entertaining professor I've ever had. Always willing to answer questions and makes sure students understand the material. The chalk throwing never got old. Not many professors leave a lasting impact on me, but Professor MacGilvray definitely did in such a positive way!
Fantastic!!!!

It's entirely possible to get an A in this class - but it won't come easy. There's lots of reading, and it's important to know how to tie all the concepts together. It's a good class and I've learned a lot, but it requires effort.
Great class! He is very hyper and that makes the material enjoyable to learn.

I'm in my last year, and Dr. MacGilvray has easily been my favorite professor at OSU. He doesn't have powerpoint slides or even any detailed notes. His class is very discussion based and he uses it to explain some very dense readings. it's definitely not an easy class, but it's truly opened my eyes to so much in the field of Political Science.

The first week you may think that since there is no homework, you can skip and pass no problem... you'd be wrong. The detail in the lectures that he provides cannot be made up by attending the review seasons. Theres is no way to fake your way through his tests. Lots of reading required but it becomes easier to understand after discussion.
Throws chalk every time he references something on the board, very funny in lecture, very clear about exams

Pop quizzes over readings. Only two other grades, a midterm and a final where you just write everything you can possibly remember. He had no clear criteria for the assessments so you have no idea what he wants or where you went wrong, but did give a study guide, and curved well. He's an amazing lecturer, though. Review sessions are a must.

One of the hardest classes i've ever taken. His test format is absolutely brutal and if your mind has a tendency to wander like mine does, its really tough. But if you pay attention to everything he says and do the readings, you'll be okay

Theory can be difficult, this much is true, but sometimes it feels like Prof. MacGilvray makes it as difficult as possible. Class is dragged on by his harsh implementation of the Socratic method, there are no slides/notes so you MUST attend, he gives pop quizzes constantly, and tests are a nightmare. Glad I like this stuff and at least he's nice.

Dr.  is the chillest professor I have ever had. His exams are crazy easy and even though he has a final paper and a final exam, you basically write all of the final paper in recitation throughout the semester and he will tell you word-for-word what to say for some parts. He does do assignments in class for participation. SUPER EASY CLASS.

its only the 2nd month of classes and this class is extremely hard I'm very lost the final research paper is on strikes and thats what the class is based on, I already want to drop it. Recitation sucks as well
This is literally the easiest class ever.  even tells you how to correct your papers for a better grade if you need to improve your scores.
Great professor, easy, willing to help with anything, gives extensions if you contact him
is a very nice professor. He will answer any and every question you have and is overall very helpful. He seems to be an easy grader. I highly recommend him.

's a nice guy, and he grades quickly and very fairly. He's got a good sense of humor and responds to emails incredibly fast. While his rubrics and tests are clear, he doesn't describe assignments well. Very repetitive, mind-numbing lecture. It's offputting that the course totally revolves around his research, but not a bad option overall.

Dr.  is one of the best profs I've ever had. He is easy-going (I slept through class one day when we were supposed to turn in an assignment and he left me turn it in that afternoon with no point deductions) and nice. He can be a bit confusing with assignments, but he tells you exactly what will be on the tests.

Great teacher. He makes everything clear and I liked the class a lot. Shouldn't be a hard class as long as you show up and read the textbook. He doesn't use slides so make sure you go to class. I learned a great deal from him. Highly recommend.
He is a very good teacher and I liked him a lot. Yo will learn and he will reward you with a decent grade if you show up... Good teacher!!!

He's truly one of the good guys. If you take  , you're taking a course with a passionate guy that loves his kids. He's always in a good mood and while he's not super easy, he wants you to learn. He's also the prof. who will nearly always return your e-mail more quickly than you would ever expect.

He is very passionate about what he teaches and even though his field may not appeal to everyone, he makes the information interesting. He is extremely helpful and he gives very clear notes. As long as you go to class and the recitations there is no way you can fail.
He is a very clear teacher who does a good job of making sure the class understands the content and the assignments.
Class is boring but easy to get through. Final paper is not fun, very boring, he is not particularly helpful with the outline, tells the class multiple things

Not a bad class at all. Lectures are a boring but just go and you will get an A. As for the final paper, make sure you start it early. The literature review and other things can be done way ahead of schedule.

is great. He loves to help. He responds to emails very quickly. Yes, his lectures are boring, but he does his best with the material he needs to cover. The final paper on strikes was a drag, but I learned some new things. I'd take his class again.
Great prof! Likes to help whenever possible. Good lecturer. Final research proposal only on strike activity so kinda on the yawn side of interesting.

He's a pretty good teacher. He's a newer professor, so he's still getting the hang of lecturing and whatnot, but he does pretty well with making things clear by using examples and exercises to show us how it can be used. Only thing I don't like is for the research paper at the end, he makes you do it on strikes, nothing else.

I loved dr.  & her class, but the grading rubrics could be confusing. attendance is worth 20/200 points, I usually didn't go to class even though it was mandatory, but still got a 100. There is a big project due at the end of the semester, but you work on it the whole semester so its basically done at the end. Exams are really easy too!

She is great! She lets you miss 6 lectures a semester, the TAs and very responsive and approachable, and her exams are very straightforward. If you come to the lecture and pay attention, you'll get an A.

This course was VERY disorganized. Clearly,  cares about teaching, but the Carmen page was impossible to navigate. Even as someone who normally adapts well to adverse learning environments, I thought it was challenging just because of the lack of guidance/no clear expectations given to us. I would not recommend this class.

Easy class. Except huge catch. If you have any traumatic event happen in your life that prevents you from participating as much or asking for an extension, expect zero sympathy and an extremely insensitive response. Just tell student advocacy instead to avoid this issue.
Very easy class. She was a good lecturer however could get very off-topic fast.
Super easy class and Dr.  shows that she cares about her students

Best professor. Chapter quizzes through Pearson (I finished all of mine in one day), 3 exams (all easy As), 10 discussion posts (easy), 1 final paper, 1 bonus paper, and bonus points on each exam. Really great class, you can work ahead, and will pass with an A. Genuine feedback and I highly recommend. I took it SU21, asynchronous and online.
I took the four week class, and there was work due every day. It was incredibly interesting and there were lots of opportunities for extra credit. I would absolutely take this professor again!

Professor  is one of my all-time favorite professors. She's very knowledgeable, understanding, and inclusive to all students. If material ever gets too heavy or triggering, she's totally cool about letting you sit out of the lecture. She's very easy to talk to, and she grades fairly as well. Study guides make the exams pretty easy too.

is great, she makes the class material fun and tells you exactly what you will need to do in order to do well in the class. You have to go to lectures since the notes are not filled out online and she takes attendance, but they are a great time and even more fun if you participate.

Honestly love  and want to take her again. You do a cool research project all semester and they walk you through it step by step by writing a series of papers. You have to show up to lecture to do well, but her exams were easy and she drops the lowest one. She makes the topic a lot more interesting!

I find  to be an incredible teacher with a thorough understanding of the world around her. She acts 'human' which goes a long way when it comes to learning the material in class. A little disorganized sometimes, but she makes up for it with stimulating lectures and the promotion of open discussions between classmates.

I took  for 4508 and 4610, and she's definitely my favorite professor in the sociology department. The material is relatively easy but stimulating, she lays out everything for the semester in the syllabus, exams are fine as long as you study a bit and pay attention. Final projects in both classes were easy. Wonderful human, please take her.

Dr.  is a great professor. I took both her 4610 and 4508 during the same semester which was great because they tend to overlap one another. Her class is easy if you show up and take good notes. If you don't show up, it's likely you won't do well on the exams. Both classes are super interesting and she teaches them well, I highly recommend.

Dr.  is one of the best professors I've had at OSU. Her 4610 class is graded by three exams (1 dropped) and a large final project. She's fairly easy on her grading and the exams aren't bad if you show up to class (she does take attendance). Outside of class, she is extremely approachable and funny. Highly recommend her to anybody!
I highly recommend her! I took three classes (Sociology 2330, 4508, and 4610) with her and she is an amazing professor. She cares about her students and her classes are very interesting.

is amazing! Her classes are interesting, applicable and easy to follow. Her teaching style is great and she really cares about her students understanding the topic and stretching their minds. I took her again the semester after I had her for a class and would take her again every semester if I could. Take a class with her!!

A really awesome lecturer and class! There's only three grades: attendance, a research paper, a PowerPoint presentation. But he doesn't take attendance, and the other two are on topics of your choice, due at the end of the semester. Even though you don't really need to go, his lectures are still super interesting and worthwhile to listen to.
The best class have taken.

He is super easy. You just have some quizzes which he sends the questions out a day early so you just show up and fill it out. He has required workshops but doesn't take attendance (but can be fun). Midterm and final are easy. Basically just a pretty easy class where you learn some useful things.

My favorite professor Ive ever had. All his papers are super clear on what he expects and hes super laid back. He grades pretty harshly but gives a lot of really great feedback. His lectures are really clear and to the point. Hes very lenient on attendance and homework deadlines.

This is the second class I have had Phil for and he is by far one of the best professors I've had. He's a tough grader but our exams are take home so he should be. He is always willing to help and constantly encourages students to stop by during office hours.

I did not think I would like her or the class but I was wrong! Great class if you're interested in law or CJS. Straight forward lectures; clean, to the point slides and class almost always ends 15 min early. It takes work to get an A but its nothing unmanagable. Study guides cover everything on the exams! Exams: MC + ID terms and short answers.

Midterm (35%), final (35%) (noncumulative) and paper (30%). Gives out very detailed study guides for the exams which have around 40 MC questions and 10-15 short answer. Paper is over a famous court trial in the 20th century. Material covered in class is very interesting. Focused on the criminal justice system. Put in the time in and get the grade.
Professor McGraw is a great lecturer. Her notes a clear and she tells you exactly what she is looking for. Plus class was usually only an hour long! She provides an overly detailed study guide.

I really can't say enough about this professor. I found her to be very intelligent and engaging, and I found the course material to be relevant and applicable as a great intro to law. The reading is the lecture, and the lecture is very well structured. Attend the class. If you do the work in this class, you get the grade.
great professor got promoted to chair so wont be teaching for a while

I find it hard to believe that she didn't learn students names in the aformentioned class...because in my class of 60+ she knows a good deal of names (maybe you just have to participate.) Great prof...515 is a very interesting class.
Assigns a lot of work, but exams and grading are very reasonable. If you get to know her, you'll think she's fabulous.
Wonderful prof. One of the best at Ohio State!

is excellent, he really cares about his students, and is funny in class. I wasn't the biggest fan of the class, but that is not fault of his -- he is very accommodating and his grading rubrics are pretty clear for both papers and exams. Lots of reading, but he does a great job clarifying confusing readings. A fairly easy A given the work.

Ben is an absolutely amazing professor. He cares about his students SO much and is incredibly understanding of mental health. This class has a lot of readings, but you can get away with skimming them as long as you pay attention to his lectures.

Great class! A lot of reading, but it's worth it if you are interested in political theory. Assignment feedback was very helpful, especially on papers. He made a graduate level class accessible to all of the students who took it (including undergrads and Program 60 students). Very understanding about his students' pandemic-related struggles, too.

I love him *so* much! Ben is so nice and funny and helpful. I had a blast in his class and he is so smart. Yeah, you might not get As on all the papers, but there are more than enough points to make up for it. Lots of extra credit too, makes up for the pop quizzes (drops the worst ones). Honestly such a cool dude. Love him, wish it was my major.

Though he presents information in odd orders,  McKean was an amazing professor to have for Intro to Peace Studies. He is very thorough in his lectures, and he actually inquires students on their thoughts on theories, and he makes an effort to understand their opinions. He gives you the final questions before the exam as well.

McKean is really great, he knows a crazy amount about what he teaches. Also just generally, the class let's you see a lot of things in a new light, things you might be tuned out to (green movement, sweatshop workers). Also, if you don't do the reading or didn't understand it, he makes it very clear in class what the major takeaways are.

Ben is a tough grader, but he is very inspiring and compelling. Of the classes I've had thus far, he is definitely the best professor that I have had. There is a ton of reading for the class, but usually the information was decently interesting. You will learn a lot if you just put forth the effort.

This was probably the best college course I've ever taken; very interesting, lots of new ideas, great teacher. The reading is tough, but he's forgiving on grading IMO. If you do the reading and make an honest effort on the essays you will get a good grade.

One of the best professors I've had. Extremely passionate, extremely helpful. Very globally aware and fun to talk to in general. If you're interested in PS, you will love his class. That being said, he grades somewhat difficult but you will learn a LOT. Put in the work and you will be fine. Don't skip class, participate, and READ THE TEXTS.

No rubrics are given for papers or assignments and lectures are very unclear. Do not expect any clarity or meaningful communication, you are on your own. She offers a good amount of extra credit, so pulling an A isn't too hard.

I'm baffled by other reviews. This class is one of the easiest A's I've ever had. Exams are super straightforward and you only have to write a few short papers. Sure the lecture notes are incomprehensible on their own but Dr. McKoon is plenty clear during class. Paper grading is also a little arbitrary, but bonus assignment makes up for this.

Majority of the final was related to memory/priming etc., rather than what we were supposed to learn; research methods! As a senior psych student, this is one of the worst classes I've attended in my academic career. Away like the plague as they say.
Unclear directions and whimsical grading system. Assignment instructions do not match how they are graded.

The homework assignments are very difficult and he tried to flip the class so he could do less work in my opinion. He made things political that didn't need to be political, especially for the type of class that it is. Just overall, not a good class. 10/10 don't take unless you absolutely HAVE to.

Dave was the best teacher I have had in a while- always accessible outside of typical hours and really cares about his students. He tries so hard to help his students and is really flexible. He is super knowledgeable about what he does and I respect him a lot. Lectures are kind of boring, but its not that interesting of a class to begin with aahah

I feel that Dr. 's Psych 4510 was difficult, but manageable with effort. She is pretty responsive to emails with questions, which definitely helps. Almost everyone in the class receives an A or a B. She's a pretty tough grader on the writing assignments, but there are so many of them that one bad grade doesn't really effect your overall grade.

Dr.  is very energetic and funny. Makes class enjoyable and entertaining. sometimes she throws candy at us for participating. Lots of easy assignments but you get multiple tries. lots of tophat but they're easy

This class is really manageable and interesting! Dr.  is very approachable and kind. Make sure to go to lecture, as TH is important for your grade and there are in-person activities that will tank your grade if you miss them. Just go to class, do your assignments - and you'll get an A.

Dr.  is just lovely! Her lectures were as entertaining as they were informative and she's super approachable and kind. She provided a scanned/pdf format to give us a free textbook, and her assignments were super easy but still help you to learn. Make sure you attend lectures though because she does do some in-class activities and TopHat.

I did not need to buy a textbook. She is very flexible with deadlines and participation. There were no big exams just many different types of assignments. Best teacher and fun class! You can tell she wants you to do well in the class.

Got a good grade in the class, but had to work tirelessly to get it. The grading critera is unclear, the templates given are overwhelming, and little to no guidance is given before you have to write. Grading is super tough and is looked at as if you are supposed to be a PhD student. Dr.  was not good at walking us through the final paper.

This class is formatted so poorly. We are given barely any guidelines on the papers, but then graded as if we are well established professional researchers. my parent wrote a dissertation and even she doesn't understand how we are being graded so harshly as an undergrad. I honestly have no idea how anyone could have a good grade in this class.

Assignment rubrics: Not clear
 Timeline to present research: Extremely tight ie. 1 weeks to code, modify, and gather participants
 Teaching style: Just end up using a lot of Purdue Owl guides then tells you to reference it. 
 Assignments: Paper heavy, 1 paper every 2 weeks usually. Not difficult but you get no support in writing it.

Dr. 's cognitive psych class is literally the easiest class I've ever taken. Papers are practically for participation because she's not looking for the most beautiful piece of art, and all 5 online quizzes have 2 attempts to get it right. Homework is super easy too. Least amount of work I've ever had for a class in college.

Dr.  is probably my favorite professor that I've had thus far at OSU. She has a great personality and prioritizes learning over memorization and grading. She is a great in person lecturer and also provides online video lectures. She really knows what she's talking about and is really detailed with the material. Uses practical assignments.
One of the very few professors that want you to actually learn the information. She does not rely on tests to check your knowledge. Had great humor and was very caring.

Dr.  is enthusiastic, makes showing up to class worthwhile, understanding, and a great professor overall.I would highly recommend you take her if you're a psych major or need to fulfill a GE req. She is super chill and engages with her classes wonderfully. She conveys material concretely, and was very flexible pre and post pandemic.
She is the best!
Dr.  is so sweet and understanding and as long as you do her work you can get an A. She tries to make the content more fun and provides extra credit.

Dr.  is great. The class content can be dry, but she does her best to make it interesting and fun to learn about. This class was an easy A because of the sheer amount of extra credit opportunities and the fact that she drops the lowest grades from ALL categories. Quizzes and papers were easy if you watched the lectures. Strongly recommend her!

Prof.  was so caring and kind. Her class was boring, but I think thats just because I dont find the topic interesting. Regardless, she was always so accommodating, and honestly the class was rather easy. You basically do activities for your grade.

One of the most enjoyable classes Ive had at osu. The homework is always easy and interesting. Quizzes were all open note with no time limit and she offers extra credit. Dr  is quick to answer emails and her lectures were always enjoyable to sit through.

This class was so easy and Dr.  was super understanding and helpful. Tons of extra credit available, she often extends deadlines, and very clear grading criteria. Exam questions were taken straight from her quizzes. Nice easy A, and you can tell she really wants her students to succeed!

Her subject is kind of boring, but she does her best to make lectures fun. She was a great professor before the COVID-19 situation, but after we went to online she was particularly amazing. She was very understanding of our situation and was always kind. She drops the lowest exams, and smaller assignments are easy. Easy, fun, definitely recommend.

She is very generous about giving high grades and it is an easy A class even if you don't study hard. She is a very nice and easy-going person who is always willing to help. But honestly the content is a bit too boring.

She gave a super tearjerker graduation speech on the last day of class, so you can tell she really cares about her students. Otherwise, her exam format is 20 multiple choice questions. It sounds straightforward, but because there are only 20 questions, you need to know the material well because there is only so much room for error.

By far my favorite professor! She is so easy going and understanding. You can easily get over 100% in the class. I will be taking 3 other classes with her next semester based off of the great experience that I had! I recommend!

I have taken both this class and organizational psych with her because she honestly grades on effort. Her assignments were very straight-forward and easy. You can tell she genuinely loves her students and what she teaches.
Dr.  is so nice and really cares about her students!

I loved taking Dr. 's class. She has awesome and interesting lectures and grades very easily. The semester project was very interesting and fairly easy. Overall I really enjoyed all of the material and did not stress about this class. There was weekly quizzes but they were super easy.

This is my second course with Dr.  and I wish I could take a third! Dr.  is kind and compassionate. She is clear with her assignment requirements and wants her students to succeed. Dr. 's class brightened my day. If you take her course, attend lectures to fully benefit from her teaching!

Loved Dr. 's caring and positive engergy. The professor provided advice for graduate school that helped me in my entrance interviews. Being able to select my own topic and work on my own research led me to discover my desired area of focus in psychology. Highly recommend and would take again if I wasn't graduating.

It's mostly lectures and group work in class. The syllabus didn't match the class at all, which made it really confusing. She's really nice and helpful with questions, and lenient overall. The grading felt all over the place though, wouldn't take again.

Psychology of Emotions class is my second class with Dr.  this term. I actually fell behind due to a personal issue. She was so kind with helping me get back on track with exceptional empathy. We've touched on every emotion this term...we learned how to create and savor good emotions and how to cope together with difficult emotions.

Positive Psychology with Dr.  is my 3rd class with this professor. I'm planning to enroll in her class this summer too. She is always passionate about the topics and offers opportunities to practice psychology skills in class. Always very kind. I learn about my ways of thinking and also about how to help other people. Highly recommend!

Dr.  was an amazing instructor! She always teaches the information clearly and makes the topic fun to learn. I learned a lot from this class. Professor  was passionate about both the course material as well as helping her students. I am very happy I took it as I learned a lot.

very kind person with a truly big heart, genuinely cares for all her students learning and wellbeing. really has a great way of orating, especially to such a large class audience, still asking questions and listening to students. i appreciate her positive attitude which was an uplifting part of my day. i also appreciate her leniency with deadlines.

took on the task of teaching this new course, and I think she did an excellent job of doing so. 
 Dr.  was very communicative in what exactly we had to do, and always greeted us with kindness and a smile. She always encouraged us to ask questions about the material, and she did a great job of explaining everything. Just loved her.

A gem of a human being, Dr.  was absolutely amazing. I had horrible health issues this semester. She made accommodations immediately and was the reason I was able to finish school. Easy to learn from, encourages independent thought, never hesitates to help. I had a lot of great professors, but Dr.  is best of the best in psychology.

This is my second class with Dr.  and I enrolled in more courses next semester with her. She is absolutely amazing and opened me up with self analysis. She has the kindest heart and truly cares about her students. I look forward to going to her class!!! I always look for her name when signing up for classes because that's how awesome she is.

This class was my breathe of fresh air this semester, go with the flow. There were no strict deadlines. Lecture sparked some heated discussions, but was very interesting to see my classmates views. The only assignments were weekly discussion boards which in turn were copy and pasted into my final project as they are used as the building blocks.

This is my second time having this professor and I really appreciate the format with which she organizes her classes. Lectures are group-oriented and there is a lot of interaction. This professor is a fair grader and is always in a joyful mood.

This is a class for the new GE, so this was her first time teaching it. The course itself was very boring and mundane, but Prof.  was up for the challenge and did her best to teach to us. She is extremely kind-hearted and very communicative, and a very kind grader. Hated the class, but Prof.  definitely made it easier to bear.

The summer course for Theories of Personality is online and has a relaxed vibe for learning comfortably. Topics are interesting. Dr. helps you create your own ideas for research on personality topics you enjoy. I will submit my final course paper for my grad school portfolio.

Dr  is my absolute favorite professor of all time. I already took her classes and specifically signed up for another one because of how much I enjoyed her teaching style. Not only is she super organized but she genuinely encourages thought-provoking conversation.  emphasizes mental health above all. Absolutely loved taking her classes
Love Dr. ! Very warm and understanding. I would take another class with her in a heartbeat. 100% recommend. She is intelligent but also fun loving in class.
This course is incredibly easy, and Quizlet will be your best friend to prepare for the exams. There are three midterms and a final.

Unlike the other sections, the exams are closed-note and in person. Personally I do not really think this is fair, as it is far easier to have notes accessible for this course- without them get ready to actually put in a good deal of work. Dr.  is really nice, but I would look for another section.

was the most caring professor I've ever met! He genuinely cares about all his students and will go out of his way to help you succeed. His lectures are fun and engaging and he thoroughly explains any questions we have. With that being said his exams are a but difficult because you have to remember many equations and understand all material.

Dr.  is a gentleman. I almost couldn't make it to a midterm because I was stuck in another state, but he let me know we could work things out. I also didn't go to class that often but still got a good grade. As long as you put in the effort, you'll get an easy A for sure.

SO NICE. You can tell he REALLY wants you to succeed and will do anything in his power to make that happen. Class participation is important as it lets him know what he can do to help and also shows that you're listening but he is so, so nice. He deserves professor of the year honestly

He is very passionate and cares about his students and teaches in multiple teaching styles so that everyone can understand the content. There's opportunities for extra credit and resources to do well in the class.
Was the sweetest man I have ever had as a teacher. Very understanding and class was great and easy.

One of the kindest people I have ever met. I don't think I've ever been more excited to attend a class than I am his. If you have him, you are blessed. He is open to literally any questions, moves at a pace that is good for everyone, and truly wants to get to know you. Truly the embodiment of a professor who is aware of mental health.

I had this professor for research methods and data analysis and enjoyed both of them! This is one of the best professors I have had at OSU. Professor  really cares about everyone and is ready to help if you have questions. The class is also really organized and super clear. Not too much homework and the tests were fair.

I was excited to take Professor 's class because of his good reviews but I was very let down by him. He is extremely hard to ask questions as he does not give you a straight answer to be "fair for everyone". I tried asking questions for clarification but it never helped me so I gave up on asking him. I wouldn't take any of his classes again.
Awesome guy, awesome teacher, peal of professing abilities

GOAT in human form. I truly do not know why this professor doesn't have a perfect rating. He is knowledgeable about the content and truly cares about his students. Dr. is a paragon of virtue among a sea of miserable, overworked, and on-edge professors.
GOAT in human form.
He TRULY cares about his students

I was blown away by how compassionate Dr.  was, and by how open he was to questions. You can tell that he legitimately cares about his students and making sure that you understand the material. The class can be tricky but Dr.  structures lectures so that everyone has a chance to ask any questions, and he works hard to answer them.
Professor  is awesome! He really cares about his class and making sure everyone understand the materia thoroughly. I would 100% recommend and plan to take another class with him in the future.

professor  is easily one of the best profs ive had at osu. he is super caring towards his students and genuinely wants nothing but success for his students. he always strives to make sure that everyone is accommodated.

is an amazing professor and you should definitely take his classes. He is extremely clear and really wants his students to succeed. Asking questions after class and taking advantage of office hours is a good resource for his classes because he is super helpful one on one. Test questions are clearly worded and he gives tons of resources.

Hard to fall behind. Go to class, ask questions. Not necessary to read textbook-he covers it all in lecture. Debatable if I'd take again as it was painful to stay awake in class.  is so thorough I couldn't pay attention to his lengthy explanations. Not sure it's a bad thing that he covers material at snail speed though-made class very easy!
Dr.  is the best. Very intelligent, yet a great teacher as well. Learned a lot from him

Bill is both a great guy and a great professor. He is a certified genius in his field but doesn't come off as a know it all. He cares a lot about both the course content and his students and wants you to do well while actually learning. The outbreak investigation is a good amount of work, but that hard and actually pretty fun overall.

in my opinion is one of the most underrated professors I have ever had. He was a great lecturer, beginning of course is kind of theory heavy, however, the class was interesting and he always explained things clearly and in a snarky funny way. Would definitely recommend taking his class. Not especially difficult either!!

was definitely the best professor I have ever had. He's very quirky and helps you understand the material in a funny way. As long as he sees you're putting forth an effort, you will pass his class. There are a lot of readings so make sure you do them or you will definitely struggle.

The fans understand his stuff; they have the intellectual capacity to truly appreciate him, to realise that he says something deep about LIFE. As a consequence people who dislike  truly ARE idiots- of course they wouldnt appreciate, for instance, the humour in  existential catchphrase "it's a feature not a bug."

Really engaging, and in a class that's centered around the President, he makes a concious effort to stay as nonpartisan and unbiased as possible. He is extremely engaging, and present his leftures in a way that makes you think. My favorote class I've taken so far, and one of the most fair classes I've taken. 10/10 would reccomend this professor.
He's really involved and is always willing to help outside of class, he never gives you the answer but gives you the info and tools to figure it out for yourself. Really great guy!

I think this professor gets a bad rep. He is a very tough grader and I struggled on the first exam but was able to recover. If you seek out the help, he's there for you when you do. AMAZING lecutres, corky and funny. Really engages the students. I lowkey love going to this class. Attendance notmandatory but I highly recommend going. no textbook

like most PA classes, he assigns research papers for each class. He does however have quizzes each class over readings. I personally don't recommend taking this class if you want to gain something w/your PS degree. 4 essay exams, tough grader. He does allow you to use a cheat sheet(1 page). Go to class, otherwise you will not do well on the exams.

Prof  is an interesting teacher. I learn new things through our class discussions and research papers we read. Fair expectations and smart guy. We have four non-cumulative exams and one easy quiz every class just to make sure you read the research papers. He's friendly and approachable in his office hour. Has a nice room too. Commendable.
Prof.  was very knowledgeable and interesting to listen to. He wasn't at all flexible in dealing with (excused) absences though. Overall a good professor to take a class from.
Smart guy, but very unwilling to help in my opinion. If you attend class and do the readings, you should be alright. But don't expect very helpful responses if you email/ask him questions.

He is really intelligent and makes class interesting. There was a data project about one of several topics relating to the presidency: mine was about the relationship between the state of the economy and the probability for an incumbent to be re-elected. It is a really fun project, and you should get an A if you take it seriously.

Not the easiest class, but he does a great job of communicating the subject matter clearly. A clear sense of impartiality, which is necessary in discussions of presidential politics. Maybe the best teacher I've had.

Prof.  was extremely insightful and helpful. While the class can be contain lots of reading, he went beyond what most professors would in order to explain it. His exam was fair. And he's a heck of a nice guy.

This was a great class. Easy grade if you did the reading, came to class, and followed instructions. And if you do those things you actually learn a lot! What more could you ask for. Some say he picks on students, but its just sarcastic humor and he is actually pretty funny.

is an OK guy and I think he cares about his students. However, he grades oddly and bases class grade on two things. Apparently he and a group of grad. students graded the midterm and as a result, grades were all over the place. Final included a lot of "gotcha" questions that had no relevance to the big picture. Doubt he gives out many As.

This isn't high school. For a 500 level class 's expectations were reasonable. Participation points are a giveaway. It's a reward for reading. When I needed help, I went to office hours. He went to Stanford and knows his stuff. If you are intellectually challenged- this isn't your class.

Professor  is probably one of my favorite professors at OSU so far. She really cares about her students and is great at creating really informative conversations in class. Highly recommend taking a class with her!

This professor as a person was amazing. Very inspirational, but the course overall is difficult if youre just taking this for a GE Credit. She is always willing to help out after hours and during office hours. You could utilize her expertise efficiently, especially as a newbie to the polisci world. She would make things easier for you if you ask.
Standard upper division IR course except this one comes with frequent reading quizzes that consist of vague questions worth 0.5 pts each for a total of 3/4 pts per quiz.

Professor  is a really kind Professor and is genuinely passionate about her teachings. I didnt think the homework was too overbearing and the quizzes were pretty easy. Towards the end of the semester some of the classes got a little boring, but the material was presented well.

Professor  did an excellent job handling the course during the pandemic. It was very easy to learn the material, and her lectures were engaging throughout the semester. This class has a lot of assignments of varied type (essays, quizzes, etc), but no assignment ever felt like it was busywork.

Professor  is SUCH a genuine and helpful woman. Really knowledgable about global politics and wants to make sure her students don't just do well in the class, but gain a true understanding of the topic. The class had a decent amount of writing assignments, but they were all doable; class takes effort but an A isn't hard to achieve.
Very inspired by her work. She is always excited and ready to talk about politics. As someone who isnt interested in politics, i was made a little interested because of this professor

is a nice person and knowledgable prof but there are just TOO many assignments in this class. Movie responses, papers, short essays, group projects, etc. I feel like with all the stuff she throws at you it's hard to keep your head above water, especially in the midst of a pandemic.

Professor  is a great professor. Shes obviously very knowledgeable about what she teaches, and shes very kind and understanding. Only complaint is that there are a lot of papers- it seems like theres always something due for this class, especially in the second half.

This is the most boring political science class I have ever taken. Lectures are very boring and she delivers everything as if it's incredibly profound, but it just doesn't make sense. Work level is manageable, papers aren't too bad, and there is a big group project/simulation at the end. Would be bearable if lecture wasn't so boring.

I've never had any professor throw as much work at me in one class. Usually they pick a medium: tests, papers, group projects, movies, quizzes-- No In this class, its all of the above. I am drowning. 6 papers total. have to watch 2 movies. big group simulation. the content is fascinating but i can't keep my head above water with her expectations.

She was alright. She gives you the whole test to review a week before each exam. There's reading quizzes and group work so you kinda need to go to class. My main issue was she didn't use much visual aid; you really need to be a good auditory learner to succeed in class. I liked the movie-viewing hw! She seems pretty passionate about IR.

A great professor, but it's sometimes hard to concentrate because it is all lecture-based and can be boring. Make sure to go to lecture and take notes because there are lecture questions on the exams. Generally gives you what is going to be on tests, which is helpful.

Dr.  was pretty middle of the road for me. The class was really dry even for someone who loves Political Science, but she's super straightforward about what she wants you to know and what the exams will look like. Don't take this if you aren't interested in PoliSci, but if you are you should find this relatively easy.
is a great professor who is passionate about global politics. Buying the book is necessary, although you do not have to read 100% of it--but very helpful to read in preparation for an exam.

GO TO CLASS. It's not hard, but there aren't notes online and they ask questions on exams about things discussed in lecture. There are 3 exams and 2 short papers, no homework. The book is helpful. My only complaint is her lack of visual aids. No powerpoints or notes, just her talking and writing on the board. Don't take if you can't auditory learn.

She is so amazing!! I love this woman. She is so smart and helpful, and is so great to just talk to about life. She is so clear in lectures and very engaging. I used the textbook in this class purely as a study aid for when I had to miss class-- attend lectures and office hours and you will get an A!

was an amazing professor for the Political Science 1300 course. She gave unbiased lectures and represented all sides of global arguments. If you are looking for a great teacher who is willing to help you learn then you should consider anything taught by Professor .

Really clear lectures with outlines available online. Super important to show up to class and at the very least skim the book. Prepare for the tests using the study guide she gives a week in advance and its pretty hard not to do well.

A very interesting class, and he made it easy to learn and stayed intrigued with. You have to read the book, because a lot shows up on the exams, which you will do more than fine on if you go to class for notes (not posted online, so you have to go every time), and read over the book material. Really great class, and I recommend him to all.

Dr.  was a great prof and I loved attending class. He was funny and kept things interesting but the tests were super hard. Reading the book is VERY important and without reading you definitely won't do well. There are no other grades besides 3 exams and a project so it was hard to get your grade up if you did poorly.
Really nice old man, interested in what he is teaching and makes if fun sometimes; test questions a little ambiguous

Though Dr.  doesn't post class notes and reading is completely necessary, I enjoyed this class and his teaching style. The notes were not too extensive and easy to jot down in class. He is a really nice guy who is very willing to give help. He words his test questions weird, but as long as you go to class and read (a must) you'll do fine.

I took 4551 & 4555 with him this semester. Attendance isn't mandatory, but it does help a lot to attend. His exams are pretty difficult as well, but as long as you have a general idea of the studies presented in class, you'll be fine. He also has an awesome curve. I failed the 1st exam horribly and still ended up with a B. overall, good prof.

The class and material were interesting, but I found that his lectures could get really tedious, and his exams were extremely difficult. He words things in a confusing way, and I often found things on the tests that were not discussed in the book or in lecture.

is a fantastic prof. His lectures are easy to follow and very interesting and he does his best to have discussions with the class. He's always willing to help with class work or anything you want to talk about. Reading the book is a must, though. Tests are half lecture, half text book material. Overall he's amazing!

I thought this class was fantastic. Dr. Monetmayor is very interesting and presents the information very clearly. Reading the book is a must and the tests are challenging but I would definitely recommend this class.

Dr.  is absolutely wonderful. He is entertaining, interesting, and always open to discussion. He will answer any questions for you after class and he posts all of his powerpoints online. Although he does not take attendance, I would highly recommend attending his lectures. And reading the book is a must! Take his class if you can.

The material itself is great! He presents the material in an entertaining way. The tests are really hard even if you read the book. I ended up with a B and went to class every day and asked questions. Still I would recommend this class!
He was a good professor. I learned a lot from him, but the class itself is hard. You have to read the book but there is no indication of what you'll be tested over.

The class was okay. Lectures not posted online, mostly studies and their results. Exams a lot harder than lecture, lots of material from the book. Not a lot of guidance for what to expect on the exam, but two small easy papers help your grade a little bit. Probably my least favorite class I took this quarter but it definitely could have been worse.

I love Dr. . He's a really good teacher and you will learn alot from him and not be bored. You do have to go to his lectures because he doesn't like to put up slides online. You do have to read the book, his tests are are based half on lecture and half on the book. It's not an easy A but any of his classes are definetely worth it.

I took 551 with this guy and it was hard but i still did well and liked it. Now 555 is way hard. The text book is just a regular book. and he makes it sound like he'll pull obvious things from it but there were questions on things i didn't even remember reading. I'm not saying don't take the class cause it is interesting. But be ready to study.

Very funny and interesting guy. His lectures are easy to pay attention to, and very helpful for the exams. His exams, however, are ridiculous and very hard. In his 20 years of teaching, he's only handed out 3 perfect scores on the exams. Reading the text and studying his notes thoroughly is a good way to go.

The class wasn't all that interesting, but was required by my major. He's a nice guy with a great sense of humor that keeps the class interesting. You do need the book for sure though. He uses an open discussion format in lecture and many things in the text will be on the exams but not covered in class.

This class would be easy if you had the time to put into it but I would advise not to take it with three other classes. Very nit picky about exam questions. I second this comment to a tee: "He doesn't take attendance ... didn't leave much of an impression on me."

He's a cool guy. I appreciated that he didn't just straight out lecture but asked us our thoughts and answered questions as he went along. Interesting material as well. I didn't find his exams as hard as some of the other comments are saying, but do make sure you read the assigned readings. Good class, good professor.
Great professor. Lots of interesting material about teenagers. Funny stories. Grades on the curve, so your grade depends on what other people get. Fair, but hard

He's very knowledgeable, well known in his field and has a lot of creative, unconventional ideas. Important to keep up with the readings as the midterm (33%) and final (67%) heavily focus on the reading (of which there is a lot). Has an amusing, wry sense of humor which keeps lectures fairly interesting. Definitely worth taking, but tough.

A lot of reading. Tests are extremely specific and difficult (look at previous exams for types of questions) but there's a very significant curve. TAKE THIS CLASS! even though some lectures can be dry, he is incredibly knowledgeable and you will learn so much. great professor

Prof.  is clearly very knowlegable on the subject and I thought the class was very interesting. The slides in class are next to useless, and the exams are mostly on what he says in class and the books you are required to read. The books, esp. the one he wrote are easy to read and very informative, my favorite poli sci class yet.

Lectures are difficult to follow since they randomly just jump around subjects. He posts his slides online so I just printed them and took notes on the print outs. For the final I read all the readings he assigned in about two days and got a A on it since most of the essay questions were from the readings.

This guy really knows his stuff. He is incredibly knowledgeable in his field. The problem comes in his tests; they are really hard and incorporate very little from class. If you do all the readings, then re-read them, and then go to his office hours and talk about them, you will do all right on the tests.

I REALLY enjoyed the class and the way he taught. He was awesome and is extremely intelligent. I would definitely recomend not only taking a class with him but going to office hours to talk to him. Hes a really nice guy and was extremely helpful when i had questions.
Tests are ridiculous, he doesnt prepare you for them at all.

Very very intelligent. Has written several books on this topic. Knows a ton. Need to attend class to have much of an idea of what's going on. Lectures are pretty good, but sometimes can get boring and he likes to go off on tangents occassionally. Not easy, but not difficult either if you pay attention. I got a B on the final and didn't read.

This man is EXTREMELY intelligent and knowledgable. However, the tests are so hard that my 62% turned into a B+ after the curve. Its rediculous to make the class that hard, but in the end, if you pay attention in class then you'll receive the grade you deserve.

This class is NOT difficult. The tests are a bit hard but the curve is huge and if you pay attention, do the reading, and study you should do fine on them without the curve anyway. This class is definitely worth your time.
thank god for the curve in the class!!!!!!!!!!!!
I think that I am in the previous reviewer's class. In fairness to Prof. , there is a pretty good curve on the midterm. It makes up for the difficulty on the test.
Smartest teacher I ever had at OSU. Make sure you read and go to class. You'll take a million notes. Highly recommend you take his class.
No Comments
LOTS of reading, but alot of it was redundant.. Lots of material, but a very comprehensive course... Know everything for the midterm and final. Curves well...

If you're taking 5612 as an elective for CSE, find something else. Class is run abysmally and his lecture slides are the worst I've seen at OSU by far. His lectures are damn near impossible to follow, as he goes on tangents about his conferences or his college life. He's a nice guy, but don't take his class if you actually want to learn something.

Tough but fair, one of my best professors yet! You will not regret taking his class, but you should regret not taking the time to learn the material. Ignore reviews on his accent, he is well spoken. He is fair and upfront about the grading scale, but it is tough. I found he is the best instructor of PSYCH3312. Also READ READ READ, the book is good!

People either love or hate Dr. . He is incredibly passionate about the material he teaches, so he tends to touch on all the developing topics he's excited about, even if they aren't related to class material. If you love the material you're learning, you will definitely enjoy his classes; if you're going since it's required, then likely not.

He gave lots of extra credit and easy going. No attendance. HOWEVER, this course is NOT EASY AT ALL! Though it's a psychology course, it almost all about neural networks. For passing this, you must know programming (use MATLAB), multivariable calculus, linear algebra, and more. HE IS THE ONLY CHOICE IF YOU WANT TO TAKE THIS COURSE. So, be prepared.

Only teaches concepts in class and says only basic math is required. You need to know calculus. If you don't already know how to code you'll struggle. We all struggled through the homework. Luckily there were a few knowledgeable people in the class. He did give relaxed grades on some of the homework and projects though.

He is an amazing person. Really nice and understanding. He cares for all of his students, and encourages people to visit him outside of class to talk about their interests. His lectures, however, were monotone and it was easy to fall asleep through. Thankfully, he is very clear with what he expects the students to know on both exams and papers.

This class is manditory, so I would suggest keeping up with your math. The grading is pretty strict but otherwise he's a cool guy. You'll receive extra points for questions that "spark" the intellect, and that he likes. He'll help you out if necessary. Don't feel shy to visit him at office hours.

Despite his accent he is able to communicate the material thoroughly, speaks better english than most native speakers. Learnt a great deal in his class as he encourages and spends time explaining things if you come halfway. Is very rigorous and knowledgeable but not inflexible, I have had him as an advisor so I know. I recomend meeting him halfway

Kind of a hard class. The second midterm was really hard for most students, but he ended up curving the class in the end. He didn't do a great job of teaching the material for the second midterm, and the TA's weren't very helpful when we asked questions about the material either. In the end it worked out, but still a tough class to get through.

This class was way too hard for a 2000 level. The lecture videos were only 10 ish minutes and didnt really help me understand anything. Quizzes were really difficult and I went over material multiple times. He didnt give me any feedback on my essays and gave me a really low grade, so I didnt have any way to improve for the final.

His online lectures are amazing & a lot of his quiz questions are phrased word for word on what he said in lecture. Ive never read any of the readings and Ive done fine on his quizzes. His midterm takes a lot of questions from the quizzes so WRITE THEM DOWN. If you do the lectures and take good notes (write exactly what he says) then youre good

Professor  is a really good professor! He always emails back fast, and is very kind when emailing back. His exams are based on in depth responses which the readings are critical to getting a good grade! The quizzes are fair.

He genuinely wants students to do well, and his class is not impossible. That being said, the quizzes are rather difficult for a 2000 level class. The material isn't bad and he does provide guidance for the midterm and final, but still is a rather tough grader. Not a bad class, but certainly not an easy A.

The course consists of a heavy workload of readings! A lot of weekly readings; but it is absolutely possible to get through the class only listening to his lectures. Quizzes are very specific and can be considered hard and tough. Detailed grading for essays. No homework. I do have to say that the curve for this class is amazing though.

No book for the class, he posts the necessary readings on Carmen. However, it is possible to go the whole course without reading and still get an A. Focus on his lectures and you'll be fine. Professor  was an extremely enjoyable professor who made statistics a much more enjoyable class. He involved himself in the class, and despite initial glitches in the class (CARMEN) maintained a sense of humor. His exams are straight forward IF you pay attention.

psych 320 is harder than regular stats, but prof.  put the notes online, always explained things carefully, and even had a low key quirky sense of humor. he made a boring subject enjoyable and spent plenty of class time working us through problems that would be on the tests - super helpful!!

For being a three credit hour course, he takes it a little too far. Nobody had any idea what would actually be on exam and exam questions were not clearly mentioned on study guide. It was kind of a hopefully I retained this information that he said once during this lecture type deal.

is a very good lecturer that really tried to make sure you understand the world of international relations and american foreign policy. Very engaging and can be surprisingly funny. His papers are rather difficult however and there is quite a bit of reading and quizzes to do. Does offer Extra Credit. Would highly reccomend

He has readings before every class that were accompanied by difficult reading quizzes. He never sent out rubrics so the papers we had to write were difficult and he is a harsh grader. Worst of all he missed a day of class and got rid of our exam review day in order to go over a pointless lecture at the end of the semester.

Prof.  is extremely passionate about the subject matter AND about his students. Yes, he expects a lot, but there is no way to do badly in his class as long as you genuinely try, go to office hours, and show him that you're improving. He's SO understanding of mental health/personal life stuff and is really helpful if you just ask! He's funny too.

Attendance is semi-mandatory. He grades toughly but is clear is what his expectations are. Reading quizzes are easy and a good way to pad out your grade. Interesting lectures and clearly knows what he is talking about. Readings are not overwhelming.

I loved taking his class in Spring 22. He clearly knows his stuff, he actually cares about his students, he makes his lectures interesting/entertaining, and his assignments are worthwhile. The more you participate, the more you get out of his class. His grades are a little tough, but fair. Plenty of xtra credit opportunities. Take a class with him

Very good intro to foreign policy class- definitely geared towards people with a passion or interest in the subject. His teaching really makes you think about decision making, and you have to push yourself to do well- not an easy class due to the expansive amount of content. Class is mainly reading quizzes, a paper and 2 exams.
Best professor at OSU so far. Truly valuable of class even if you do not have much to do with foreign policy. So much to learn from him and his lectures.

I suffer from general anxiety, and he is probably the most cooperative professor I've ever met when it comes to the matter. He shows a true passion for his subject matter and sharing it with his students

is just an absolute gem of a person. He is so thoughtful, caring and accommodating. I love who he is as a person, despite him being an insanely tough grader. The real issue here is the content. This class is incredibly difficult. There are mountains of readings, slides, and terms that even open note quizzes and tests can't prepare you for.

Foreign policy isn't my strong suit so I knew this class would be a challenge. Takes a good amount of engagement with the material to succeed. Lectures can be dense, note-taking has to be a strong suit. Good prof who cares about his students, just wasn't the most interesting class I've taken. Like foreign policy? Take this. If not, be prepared

I was honestly not expecting this course to be as valuable as it was. Not only does Professor  give you a great base in terms of foreign policy, he teaches you a lot of important skills in terms of writing, formulating your argument, and more. The lectures can definitely be a lot, but its a super rewarding and you truly learn a lot.

One of my favorite professors at OSU. There is a lot of reading, and he is a rather tough grader, but he is also very helpful with feedback. I would say only take this course if you're actually interested in foreign policy. The man is a great lecturer, and if you care about this stuff, you're going to get a lot out of this class.

Professor  is one of the best instructors I have had so far throughout my college career. He is a very tough grader but it made me think significantly more about the content of the class, as opposed to someone who just gave completion credit or graded with minimal effort. He obviously cares about his students' lives in and out of the classroom.

Professor  is an amazing lecturer and gives great feedback. Some people have been saying that he comes off as arrogant or condescending, but I did not get that impression at all. He just expects a lot from his students and encourages them to think through difficult concepts. The class is very reading-heavy and attending the lectures is crucial.

Go to office hours! He is a professor who will respect/help you more if you show him you care about your grade and his class. Don't hesitate to ask for help before memos/midterm/finals. Really knowledgeable and cares about foreign policy issues today. History heavy. For poly sci majors, this class will be a great foundation for future classes.

He's very passionate and clearly knowledgeable about what he teaches and expects you to thoroughly engage with the content. Hes very understanding too. Most grades are from reading quizzes and a couple papers throughout. Shouldn't take this class unless youre genuinely interested in foreign policy, but if you are and you care youll love it.
You do need to go to lecture and take notes, but the class is very interesting and not too hard. Prof  is nice and pretty personable.

This class was engaging and interesting, and Dr.  is very accessible and passionate about sociology. Her grading is extremely fair, and she created a fun classroom atmosphere and listened to students. She'll push you to expand on your answers, but she's receptive to different perspectives.
Great teacher that really cares about her students.

Mary is the best professor I've had. She is incredibly kind and understanding, so it's okay to miss class- but the material is SUPER important to get. Plan on going every lecture. The readings and topics can be difficult, but she is a phenomenal and engaging lecturer. Always well-prepared. Fascinating class! Fair grading.
just dont take it if you have other hard classes. she deducts points on not having comma on the essay.

One of the most genuine professors I've had at OSU. She really showed that she cared about us and adjusted the syllabus and assignments to make it as easy as possible for us during the pandemic. The assignments and exams are very easy as long as you do the readings and listen to the lectures (she goes over the reading's main points in lecture).
Dr. 's class is so interesting. She is extremely knowledgeable about the topic and amazing at her job. She is funny and so helpful. Highly recommend.

As an online class Professor  was terrible. She just assigned reading in the book, made us take a quiz after every chapter (15) and had 3 exams. She does not give extra credit and did not record lectures.

She is so fun and you can tell she genuinely cares about her class and students. She has tons of experience and stories and is very easygoing. She posts the learning objectives which follow the textbook, so studying for exams is very easy and she definitely isn't trying to trick you in the exams. Highly recommend taking her.

Mary is one of the funniest and most engaging professors Ive had thus far. The class is very lecture-oriented and requires you to read the textbook in order to do well on the exams, but if you study then you should be fine! Shes very passionate and knowledgeable, and its an extremely interesting class to take assuming youre interested in law!

A sweet,Lovely woman, shes really a gem and wants all her students to succeed. Show up to class, all the tests are based on the readings and lecture notes. If you want an A,SHOW UP to class. The material is hard to follow but if you ask for her help she will make sure you have a clear understanding of the material. The tests r all multiple choice

Dr.  is one of the BEST professors and faculty at OSU! He is very professional, caring, and willing to help students pass his course(s). His teaching style and compassion for students makes attending OSU worthwhile. He certainly had a positive impact on my graduate school experience. I highly recommend him! Dr.  rocks!

Dr.  has a ton of cool experience he brings to the course. I think for some the material could be dry, but he made it so interesting. I found his lectures so useful, interesting, clear, and concises that I sent them to my former health research coworkers. This was the most useful course of my MPH so far, & his expertise is critical to that.

Dr.  was great. This class was my second time having him and while he is a little monotoned, his lectures show that he a professional in his field. I learned a lot from him, and I will say that is very receptive to any and all feedback whether it be content from lectures or how the class is structured!
Good guy, wants you to learn in fun ways. Doesnt just push tests or massive papers.

this class was super interesting and I really enjoyed it! Easy A if you do the work!!! I would say I spent an average of 30 min per week on this class and got an A. The actual class sessions are super easy and lowkey.  is very kind and understanding and knowledgeable in his field. Guest lectures are usually very good as well. Class can be long

Dr.  makes this class so much fun! If you don't have an interest in PubH, don't take it. There's a paper every week, 3 short answer questions every other week, and one 3-hour presentation (not as bad as it sounds). If you do the work and put in effort, you'll get the A. But it's a lot of work

's class is kind of a unique animal. He's unbelievably intelligent and a wealth of knowledge (although he does go on a lot of long-winded tangents), and it can be tempting to skip class, but he knows who shows up consistently and who doesn't. If you go to class almost always and act at least somewhat engaged, you'll be successful.
Very boring lectures, doesn't use visual aid, grade comes down to midterm, final, research paper

Lectures not mandatory. If you read the books you don't need to go. Such a nice and brilliant man. Long paper assigned, and is expected to be heavy in statistical data. Even if you go to lecture, buy the book. It's very hard to take notes and stay focused. Great man
is an expert on Congress and highly recommended. Personable, entertaining class, and genuinely cares about his students
Dr. 's course can be challenging, but he is highly supportive of students. Well worth the effort you need to put in. He is an expert on Congress.
Dr. 's course is very challenging, but worthwhile. He is an expert on Congress and is definitely worth the time.
Doctor  is an expert on Legislative Politics. The class is rigorous, but you will learn a great deal.  is an excellent professor and is highly recommended.
grades very hard, couldn't really help with the essay
Very friendly and very intelligent, but appallingly dry lectures. He reads straight from a prepared script in a monotone voice.
Very intelligent instructor who explains things thoroughly. Only three grades in the glass. Make sure you read the books!

did a very good job teaching the course. He is very smart and this showed in his lectures. Dr.  is very passionate about legislative politics. The class is easy, though there are quite a few books (a fair amount for a 500 level class). Responds to emails very fast and is a nice person.

Though Prof.  is an amazingly nice man, I'm not sure if I could stand to sit there for 10 weeks again. The tests and essay were easy, but lectures were not at all helpful to the class. Refers you to sections of the book and spends nearly an hour talking about what poli sci majors should already know-- the political news. nice guy but do avoid
neutral
Exams are slightly hard but not ridiculous. She's a decent professor and topics are actually interesting.

The class was a positive experience, but could get dry sometimes. She read pretty much directly off the slides, but attendance was a must because we would have surprise in-class assignments which counted as an attendance grade. Grading criteria for her assignments could have been a bit clearer, but she was friendly and responsive to emails.

Dr.  is a great professor. As long as you do the reading and attend lectures, the class is very easy. She also curves the exams if many students struggle with certain questions and offers extra credit opportunities. If you do the work, it is very easy to get an A. Also, the lectures are info heavy but still interesting.

the exams are terrible. They donot even seem that hard while you are taking them, but she grades like a hound. Average of the first exam was a 68, no curve. She offers little extra credit and the only plus is she drops the lowest 8 quiz grades, but with the exams being worth 70% of ur grade it does not really matter now does it. I would avoid it.

Dr.  is a tough prof, but if you do the readings then you can do well. While there are a lot, they're very instructive on nat'lism and ethnicity. She's a brilliant scholar, and if you are thinking about research then she's a great person to ask for help. Grading is mostly exams plus reading quizzes. You get out of the class what you put in.

Dr.  is brilliant, but her class is way harder than it has to be. Super difficult reading quizzes, and lots of stuff on tests that were hardly covered. Interesting class, but I definitely would not take it again.

Dr.  taught such an amazing class. I learned so much and the assignments were sort of fun. We had a presentation and paper and I actually sort of enjoyed those. The exams also weren't bad, they were online and open note. There are small reading quizzes everyday, but if you read they are super easy. Loved this class.
This is the third class I have taken with Dr. . Although you have to work for an A, her classes will teach you a ton and she is extremely intelligent and well respected in her field.

This was the first time Democratic Erosion was offered at OSU and Prof.  did a great job with it even though it's not her area of expertise. Lots of reading (about 100 pages/wk), but workload is manageable all things considered. Hopefully OSU continues to offer this course and has her teach it at least a couple more times!
Seems to really care about how her teaching is going and how she can improve herself. Reading quizzes for each class, but they are only like two easy questions each.

Dr.  is great! She is extremely passionate and knowledgable about the material being covered. She also gave us a one sided sheet of paper as a cheat sheet for the exams. There is paper and presentation that take some effort, but its certainly not absurd amount of work. The hardest part of the course was the map quiz on Africa

She is extremely knowledgable and loves what she teaches. Class can get boring at times and she may not be as engaging but she cares about the subject a lot. She is a VERY VERY TOUGH professor in grading exams and constructing them. Be prepared to work hard. I got an A but considering the amount of coursework, the class should have been a 4000.

is a great teacher. She really wants her students to do well. She makes sure to ask students if her current teaching style is working and reworks the curriculum to help the students learn better. If you pay attention and stay on main points you'll do fine. A good person overall.

One of the best courses I have had here at OSU! Dr.  is an excellent professor and I would take anything that she taught. The lectures were engaging and fun. Not your average poli sci class, she teaches using a variety of disciplines and challenges you to think for yourself. Very helpful in office hours and gives points back on exams.

Good instructor. She's loves what she teaches and has experience. Very nice approachable and friendly. Gives pop quizzes over readings to do random attendances checks. Tests and lectures are straightforward

Fantastic professor. I took the OPEEP Psych 1100 class and although it was somewhat disorganized at times, he always made sure the students were taken care of and made sure that they have the ability to succeed. Very caring professor and a very humble person. Readings were very heavy at times, however they became easier to manage over time

Dr.  is very invested in your success. He could be driving, eating, or sleeping but he will still take the time to answer your question. It is an easy A if you follow his instructions which are clear. The course is also very organized.
Amazing professor!!! all that needs to be said

I cant begin to explain how much this professor cares about how his students are doing in the class and how much they ENJOY the class. He constantly is looking for feedback on how he can further change the course so that it can help our intro psych experience. There is extra credit literally every week and going to tutoring gets you extra credit!

Dr.  gives out extra credit like candy on Halloween. This semester, he gave out 70 points of extra credit out of 500 total points, so if you get all of the EC and try in the class, you are well underway for an A in the class.

Makes the material enjoyable to learn and easy to understand. Really sweet and caring. Totally accommodating to the students. Posts his lectures on Carmen. Gives a lot of extra credit so if you don't do well it's on you. Professor aside, he's really such a great guy and I'd strongly suggest taking him. Also, don't buy the textbook bc its useless.

Tests are straightforward. Lot's of extra credit. Don't really need a textbook and there is no online stuff which is awesome. His study sessions saved my butt and is a really nice guy and is very lenient on grading.
Boring, not necessarily hard. just really boring
Very kind professor that is very passionate about his work. Not only that, but he is very communicative and is always accepting of feedback.

This class takes effort. Attendance is important and its a lot of work. But, Dr.  puts in the effort to make the class interesting. He is passionate about the subject and cares that his students are experiencing this passion too. He encouraged my interests and helped me explore EHS careers. put in the effort and you'll be fine

After experiencing both Covid and depression and receiving a doctors note for both of these issues, Dr. would not unlock the current modules so that I could catch up and stay current in the course. Instead he forced me to continue doing them in order, even though each module is unrelated to the others. Doesn't seem to care about the students.
